WEBVTT

00:24.583 --> 00:25.916
[Judy] Bleh...

00:26.000 --> 00:28.750
Blood. Blood. Blood.
And death.

00:30.041 --> 00:31.541
[Nick] All right. You know
what? You're milking it.

00:31.625 --> 00:32.791
Besides, I think we got it.

00:33.958 --> 00:35.958
We got it up there.
Thank you, Yakkity-yak.

00:36.041 --> 00:37.333
You laid it all out
beautifully.

00:37.416 --> 00:40.250
I framed Lionheart.
I can frame you too.

00:40.333 --> 00:42.500
It's my word against yours.

00:42.583 --> 00:43.958
Actually...

00:44.041 --> 00:46.333
[Bellwether] <i>And I'll dart</i>
<i>every predator in Zootopia</i>

00:46.416 --> 00:47.333
<i>to keep it that way.</i>

00:47.416 --> 00:49.791
- It's your word against yours.
- Huh?

00:49.875 --> 00:52.000
It's called a hustle,
sweetheart.

00:52.083 --> 00:53.041
Boom.

00:53.125 --> 00:54.791
[♪ upbeat music playing]

00:55.958 --> 00:59.875
Unlikely duo Judy Hopps,
the city's first bunny cop,

00:59.958 --> 01:02.625
and Nicholas Wilde,
a small-time street fox,

01:02.708 --> 01:06.041
<i>uncovered a conspiracy</i>
<i>by Mayor Bellwether today</i>

01:06.125 --> 01:08.291
<i>using a toy carrot</i>
<i>recorder pen.</i>

01:08.375 --> 01:09.916
[Bellwether]
<i>I can frame you too.</i>

01:10.583 --> 01:12.625
[cackling, shrieks]

01:14.166 --> 01:17.291
[Growley] <i>Wilde later</i>
<i>joined the ZPD himself,</i>

01:17.375 --> 01:20.375
<i>where the pair are now the</i>
<i>very first bunny-fox team</i>

01:20.458 --> 01:22.541
<i>in the history of Zootopia.</i>

01:23.791 --> 01:26.625
New mayor and former actor
Brian Winddancer

01:26.708 --> 01:27.875
hailed the two

01:27.958 --> 01:30.583
<i>during celebrations</i>
<i>for the 100th anniversary</i>

01:30.666 --> 01:33.500
<i>of the invention</i>
<i>of Zootopia's weather walls</i>

01:33.583 --> 01:35.916
<i>that allowed all environments</i>
<i>and all animals</i>

01:36.000 --> 01:38.250
<i>to coexist in one city.</i>

01:38.333 --> 01:41.666
This is our Zootennial!

01:41.750 --> 01:43.916
And if a lowly country bunny

01:44.000 --> 01:46.291
and a shifty,
likely criminal fox

01:46.375 --> 01:49.375
can ignore
their vast, vast differences

01:49.458 --> 01:52.750
and solve bias
and stereotype forever,

01:52.833 --> 01:57.541
then maybe we can all
embrace our differences

01:57.625 --> 02:00.250
and be better zoogether.

02:00.333 --> 02:01.291
[crowd cheering]

02:01.375 --> 02:04.250
We're gonna crack a new case,
make the world a better place,

02:04.333 --> 02:06.458
and be the greatest partners
of all time. [chuckles]

02:06.541 --> 02:07.375
[Nick] Hmm.

02:07.458 --> 02:09.000
I mean,
we're not that different.

02:09.500 --> 02:10.583
[camera shutter clicks]

02:16.208 --> 02:17.958
[♪ funk music playing]

02:20.083 --> 02:20.916
[groans]

02:21.000 --> 02:22.458
[Chief Bogo] <i>At the ZPD,</i>

02:22.541 --> 02:27.250
<i>partnership</i>
<i>is the cornerstone of success.</i>

02:27.333 --> 02:29.458
You want to put bad guys away?

02:29.541 --> 02:32.416
Be on the same page.
Every day.

02:32.500 --> 02:35.750
Now today's bad guy is
this customs inspector

02:35.833 --> 02:38.875
who's been smuggling
illegal overseas cargo

02:38.958 --> 02:40.375
through the city's shipyard.

02:40.458 --> 02:43.875
Captains Hoggbottom
and Truffler will lead.

02:43.958 --> 02:46.250
Higgins, Bloats, flank left.

02:46.333 --> 02:48.083
Chèvre, Bûcheron, right.

02:48.166 --> 02:50.291
And down the middle,
the Zebros.

02:50.375 --> 02:51.250
Zebros!

02:51.333 --> 02:53.708
Hopps and Wilde, I know you're
eager to prove yourselves,

02:53.791 --> 02:56.458
but as rookies,
you will observe only

02:56.541 --> 02:59.416
and watch the veteran teams
show you how it's...

02:59.500 --> 03:00.333
[♪ music stops]

03:01.333 --> 03:02.500
Chief, hi.

03:02.583 --> 03:04.041
If you're looking
for Nick and Judy,

03:04.125 --> 03:05.791
they said they got it.

03:05.875 --> 03:09.541
And they are already on site,
with their baby!

03:09.625 --> 03:11.125
[sighs]

03:11.208 --> 03:13.166
[♪ upbeat music playing]

03:18.416 --> 03:19.666
[whispering]
Are you sure this'll work?

03:19.750 --> 03:21.625
You're the one that said
we needed a bust.

03:21.708 --> 03:23.791
Just follow my lead, okay?
Act casual.

03:23.875 --> 03:25.041
- Hey!
- Here we go.

03:25.125 --> 03:26.208
Hello?

03:26.291 --> 03:27.750
This whole area's restricted.

03:27.833 --> 03:29.083
You can't be here.

03:29.166 --> 03:31.750
Whoa. Fox and bunny. Okay.

03:31.833 --> 03:34.000
[chuckles]
Yes, but proud parents first.

03:34.083 --> 03:36.166
- Mister...
- Inspector.

03:36.250 --> 03:37.541
Inspector Snootley.

03:37.625 --> 03:40.500
Inspector? What do you do?

03:40.583 --> 03:42.291
Ensure that nothing illegal
gets smuggled here

03:42.375 --> 03:44.041
in one of these
cargo containers?

03:44.791 --> 03:46.875
That's a weird way
to ask that.

03:46.958 --> 03:49.041
Anyway, you gotta leave.
You can't be here.

03:49.125 --> 03:51.625
- Oh.
- Wait. Wait.

03:51.708 --> 03:53.458
He's right, gosh darn it.

03:53.958 --> 03:54.958
You are right, sir.

03:55.708 --> 03:58.250
I guess we should've thought
this through. Right, babe?

03:59.041 --> 04:02.250
Before we decided
to come down here

04:02.333 --> 04:05.750
to this beautiful
industrial shipyard

04:05.833 --> 04:11.458
to celebrate the big day
of our birthday boy.

04:11.541 --> 04:14.250
It's his birthday?

04:14.333 --> 04:16.583
Yeah. First one since...
[sighs]

04:16.666 --> 04:18.750
[whimpering]
...since the accident.

04:18.833 --> 04:20.375
[gasps, sighs]

04:20.458 --> 04:21.583
And, you know, the one thing

04:21.666 --> 04:23.375
this little stinker
wished for... [sniffles]

04:23.458 --> 04:26.125
...aside from one day
getting his tail reattached,

04:26.208 --> 04:29.250
was to see a choo-choo.

04:29.333 --> 04:32.791
And to maybe get a toot-toot
conductor to sign his cast.

04:32.875 --> 04:36.958
But I'm betting
a customs inspector

04:37.041 --> 04:38.041
would be even better.

04:38.583 --> 04:39.750
Really?

04:39.833 --> 04:41.750
All right.
For the kid. For the kid.

04:41.833 --> 04:43.791
Oh, you're a saint.

04:43.875 --> 04:46.166
We thank you so much.
Here you go. Either leg.

04:46.250 --> 04:48.291
Or both. I don't care.

04:48.375 --> 04:49.666
Maybe put a doodle on it.

04:49.750 --> 04:50.791
Doesn't need to be perfect.

04:50.875 --> 04:52.333
He's also legally blind.

04:56.833 --> 04:58.250
[♪ upbeat jazz playing]

04:58.333 --> 04:59.708
I put a little train there
because

04:59.791 --> 05:00.958
I know you like trains.

05:01.041 --> 05:02.666
[whispering]
Come on. Come on. Come on.

05:03.208 --> 05:04.583
- Just jiggle it.
- Yes. I know.

05:04.666 --> 05:05.500
- Hurry!
- I got this.

05:05.583 --> 05:06.916
[Nick] Jiggle it.
Jiggle it. Jiggle it!

05:07.000 --> 05:07.833
[lock clanks]

05:07.916 --> 05:09.333
[Chief Bogo on radio]
<i>Hopps and Wilde,</i>

05:09.416 --> 05:10.916
<i>you are not authorized.</i>

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
<i>Stand down</i>
<i>and wait for backup.</i>

05:14.083 --> 05:16.125
- [grumbles]
- [chuckles]

05:17.166 --> 05:18.166
Toot, toot.

05:18.250 --> 05:19.916
- It's the fuzz!
- [Judy] Stop!

05:20.000 --> 05:23.000
- Stop in the name of the law!
- Everybody run!

05:25.500 --> 05:27.458
Well, can't win 'em all.

05:27.541 --> 05:28.375
[horn blasts]

05:28.458 --> 05:30.041
Get outta the road,
you dumb bunny.

05:30.125 --> 05:32.000
Hmm. Agree to disagree.

05:32.916 --> 05:36.583
My hog rod!
This is a snoutrage!

05:39.333 --> 05:41.458
Hopps and Wilde
in pursuit of suspect

05:41.541 --> 05:43.750
in a stolen catering van
heading east...

05:43.833 --> 05:44.916
- [chuckles]
- Stop it.

05:45.000 --> 05:46.875
...heading east
through Sheepshire.

05:54.666 --> 05:55.708
[gasps]

05:58.000 --> 05:59.416
Whoa!

06:00.750 --> 06:01.750
Beautiful.

06:01.833 --> 06:03.583
I'll have what he's having.

06:03.666 --> 06:05.583
Darling,
I believe your driving

06:05.666 --> 06:07.166
is giving me some white hairs.

06:07.708 --> 06:10.000
Also, am I always gonna be
in the passenger's seat?

06:10.083 --> 06:11.833
'Cause if we're
establishing sides...

06:13.000 --> 06:14.000
Back off, rookies!

06:14.083 --> 06:15.791
Let the real teams handle it.

06:15.875 --> 06:19.625
- Ma'am, we are a real team.
- Shortcut. Take the tunnel.

06:20.291 --> 06:22.208
- [groans]
- [groaning]

06:23.208 --> 06:24.583
[hoots]

06:26.500 --> 06:27.458
[gasps]

06:29.958 --> 06:32.458
Stand down, noobs. We got him.

06:32.541 --> 06:34.333
- Rolling spikes!
- Rolling spikes!

06:43.166 --> 06:44.291
[cameras clicking]

06:45.250 --> 06:47.083
I hate that dumb bunny.
[gasps]

06:54.000 --> 06:55.375
[♪ upbeat jazz continues]

06:55.458 --> 06:56.791
Oh...

07:09.916 --> 07:11.250
- I'm gonna jump.
- What?

07:11.333 --> 07:12.291
No, no. What are you...

07:12.375 --> 07:14.875
Carrots, hey... I would like
to call a partner meeting.

07:14.958 --> 07:16.041
No, Carrots!

07:16.875 --> 07:18.083
- Judy!
- [Judy yelps]

07:25.541 --> 07:27.083
[♪ music stops]

07:27.166 --> 07:29.166
Please join me
in a moment of silence

07:29.250 --> 07:33.333
for our beloved weather wall
inventor Ebenezer Lynxley.

07:33.416 --> 07:34.416
[gasps]

07:37.333 --> 07:39.500
- [laughs]
- [both] Zebros!

07:40.000 --> 07:41.625
[sighs]

07:41.708 --> 07:43.208
- [hinge squeaks]
- Huh?

07:48.041 --> 07:49.083
[gasps]

07:54.458 --> 07:55.875
Reptile?

07:57.208 --> 07:58.333
[gasps]

07:59.750 --> 08:01.875
Chief, those two
are out of control!

08:01.958 --> 08:04.500
<i>Zootopia ain't just</i>
<i>a mammal city.</i>

08:05.000 --> 08:08.916
<i>It has a secret,</i>
<i>tiny reptile population,</i>

08:09.541 --> 08:11.333
<i>though most live abroad.</i>

08:11.416 --> 08:15.250
<i>Of course, Zootopia does not</i>
<i>allow snakes. </i>[chuckles]

08:15.333 --> 08:17.041
<i>There ain't been one of those</i>
<i>around here</i>

08:17.125 --> 08:19.000
<i>for at least a hundred years.</i>

08:19.083 --> 08:22.000
[announcer] <i>"Scales and tales</i>
<i>of the weird."</i>

08:22.083 --> 08:25.125
Yeah, not sure
Nibbles Maplestick

08:25.208 --> 08:27.625
is our most reliable source.

08:27.708 --> 08:30.791
[Chief Bogo] Bunny,
orange dog, in here now.

08:30.875 --> 08:31.916
[grumbles]

08:32.000 --> 08:34.041
[Judy] Sir, today may not
have been ideal,

08:34.125 --> 08:34.958
but the anteater was captured.

08:35.041 --> 08:36.291
By the Zebros!

08:36.375 --> 08:37.875
- Zebros!
- Shut it!

08:38.541 --> 08:39.791
[both whisper] Zebros.

08:39.875 --> 08:40.875
It was us.

08:40.958 --> 08:42.125
But more importantly,

08:42.208 --> 08:45.125
I believe we may have made
a significant discovery.

08:45.208 --> 08:48.333
The stolen van contained a
smuggled crate from overseas,

08:48.416 --> 08:49.708
pamphlets for the Zootennial,

08:49.791 --> 08:51.625
and some type of reptile skin.

08:51.708 --> 08:53.291
I've already sent samples
for testing.

08:53.375 --> 08:55.958
- And if you...
- What needs testing is you!

08:56.041 --> 08:58.375
You two tore up half the city.

08:58.458 --> 09:01.000
Because of you,
we had to call in Jumbo Unit

09:01.083 --> 09:03.083
to remove a dik-dik
from a tuba!

09:03.166 --> 09:04.583
<i>You're almost out.</i>
<i>You're gonna be...</i>

09:04.666 --> 09:06.708
<i>No! Please, no!</i>

09:06.791 --> 09:08.416
<i>Who's catching him?</i>

09:08.500 --> 09:10.125
Sorry, could you show me
that clip again?

09:10.208 --> 09:11.500
Wasn't wearing my glasses.

09:12.083 --> 09:16.083
Did you or did you not disobey
a direct order to stand down?

09:16.166 --> 09:17.666
Sir, we were in pursuit.

09:17.750 --> 09:19.500
And article 6,
paragraph B states,

09:19.583 --> 09:20.875
"If the lead officers
think that..."

09:20.958 --> 09:22.625
You are not lead officers!

09:22.708 --> 09:24.000
You're one-hit wonders

09:24.083 --> 09:25.500
who should go back
to meter maiding

09:25.583 --> 09:27.416
and slinging pawpsicles!

09:27.500 --> 09:30.125
If I may, I think
someone's just jealous

09:30.208 --> 09:31.875
that we got to drive
the squeal mobile.

09:31.958 --> 09:34.500
Or maybe you thought
it was your momma.

09:34.583 --> 09:37.583
- [squealing, growling]
- Enough! Everybody out.

09:37.666 --> 09:39.375
[grunting]

09:41.250 --> 09:42.375
[sighs]

09:42.875 --> 09:44.125
Officer Hopps,

09:44.208 --> 09:48.208
despite my best efforts
to avoid it, I like you.

09:48.791 --> 09:53.666
But this need to overdo it

09:53.750 --> 09:56.583
made both of you
a headline today.

09:57.250 --> 10:00.791
And it reflects badly on me,
on the department,

10:00.875 --> 10:02.333
and frankly

10:02.416 --> 10:06.583
on any bunny hoping
to follow in your footsteps.

10:08.541 --> 10:11.333
Not every case
is going to save the world.

10:13.083 --> 10:14.083
Knock-knock.

10:14.583 --> 10:15.583
Hi.

10:15.666 --> 10:17.166
You know, this kinda...
this sounds a lot

10:17.250 --> 10:19.291
like a... just a
"you guys" conversation.

10:19.375 --> 10:21.250
So what I'm gonna do
is I'm gonna go ahead and...

10:21.333 --> 10:24.291
Is there a reason why you
don't take anything seriously?

10:24.375 --> 10:25.708
Jokes are
a classic defense mechanism

10:25.791 --> 10:27.125
for someone with
a traumatic childhood.

10:27.208 --> 10:29.125
Would you like
a traumatic adulthood?

10:30.125 --> 10:31.125
I would not.

10:31.208 --> 10:32.541
I allowed you to work together

10:32.625 --> 10:35.666
because you did this city
a great service.

10:35.750 --> 10:38.750
But today,
you messed it all up.

10:38.833 --> 10:40.833
And now, some are questioning

10:40.916 --> 10:42.750
whether you should've been
partners in the first place.

10:42.833 --> 10:43.958
- Sir...
- So,

10:44.041 --> 10:46.541
instead of chasing
imaginary reptiles,

10:46.625 --> 10:48.166
I am pulling you
from the field...

10:48.250 --> 10:49.083
What?

10:49.166 --> 10:50.916
...and giving you
a new assignment

10:51.000 --> 10:54.500
reserved for special teams
like yourselves.

10:54.583 --> 10:59.541
Fail at this, and I will have
no choice but to split you up.

11:00.166 --> 11:02.291
There will be no more
Hopps and Wilde.

11:02.916 --> 11:06.916
But if you're as good
as you think you are,

11:07.708 --> 11:09.791
this is your moment to shine.

11:12.333 --> 11:15.500
Welcome to Partners in Crisis,

11:15.583 --> 11:18.916
a workshop for duos heading
for disaster. [chuckles]

11:19.000 --> 11:21.833
I'm your therapy animal,
Dr. Fuzzby.

11:21.916 --> 11:22.916
And you are here

11:23.000 --> 11:26.708
because mismatched pairings
often need a little more work

11:26.791 --> 11:28.708
to make them work.

11:28.791 --> 11:31.166
Greg, we talked about that.

11:31.250 --> 11:32.458
What are we making Marlon?

11:32.541 --> 11:34.916
Uncomfortable. Yes.

11:35.000 --> 11:35.833
[screams]

11:35.916 --> 11:38.041
[Dr. Fuzzby] And, Francine,
Clark may be a mouse,

11:38.125 --> 11:40.250
but he is your partner first.

11:41.416 --> 11:44.041
And we have two
new "apart-ners."

11:44.625 --> 11:46.750
Can you tell us
about your journey

11:46.833 --> 11:48.958
to dysfunction junction?
[chuckles]

11:49.041 --> 11:53.166
Well, we've been official
partners for one week.

11:53.250 --> 11:55.041
Happy anniversary.

11:55.125 --> 11:57.666
And we're not dysfunctional
at all, actually.

11:57.750 --> 11:59.916
Functioning fine.
Better than fine.

12:00.000 --> 12:01.916
And we did sort of
save the city,

12:02.000 --> 12:05.625
so us being here kinda seems
like a huge misunderstanding.

12:06.666 --> 12:08.250
Notice how she answered first,

12:08.333 --> 12:09.833
did not allow her partner
to speak,

12:09.916 --> 12:11.208
seems to be
in a state of denial

12:11.291 --> 12:13.458
and taps her foot when
she's suppressing discomfort.

12:13.541 --> 12:14.500
[chuckles]

12:14.583 --> 12:16.583
And observe the source
of her discomfort

12:16.666 --> 12:18.583
represented by
the disconnected affectation

12:18.666 --> 12:20.666
of her emotionally
insecure partner.

12:20.750 --> 12:21.583
Oh!

12:21.666 --> 12:24.583
But with hard work, they'll be
on the same page by year two.

12:24.666 --> 12:25.500
- Huh?
- Oh.

12:25.583 --> 12:28.750
But for now, let's begin
by greeting our teammate.

12:28.833 --> 12:30.291
Who would like to go first?

12:30.375 --> 12:31.500
Thank you, Joel.

12:33.208 --> 12:34.791
- [grunts, gasping]
- [snarling]

12:34.875 --> 12:36.916
Okay, unfortunately,
Karen has chosen

12:37.000 --> 12:40.250
to see Joel's smile
as a sign of aggression.

12:40.333 --> 12:43.083
Hackles down, Karen.
Karen, hackles down.

12:43.166 --> 12:45.291
Joel, the safe word
is "coconut."

12:45.375 --> 12:46.625
[Joel] Coconut!

12:48.666 --> 12:50.833
Okay, we have to set another
meeting with the Chief.

12:50.916 --> 12:52.625
Promise we'll be better.

12:52.708 --> 12:53.958
- [gasps]
- [Zebros chuckle]

12:54.041 --> 12:55.208
[whispering] Zebros!

12:55.291 --> 12:58.291
[chuckles] You talk back less.
Maybe not at all.

12:58.375 --> 13:01.875
Yeah. Or we go with my
playbook, and we just lay low.

13:01.958 --> 13:03.875
[Judy scoffs]
We cannot prove ourselves

13:03.958 --> 13:05.041
if we are stuck in that room.

13:05.125 --> 13:06.583
And if we complain
to Chief Beef,

13:06.666 --> 13:08.083
he'll just make us
stay longer.

13:08.166 --> 13:09.875
Play it smart.
Stay off the radar.

13:09.958 --> 13:11.791
And don't let it get to you.
Okay?

13:11.875 --> 13:13.958
'Cause we are the dream team.

13:14.458 --> 13:15.458
[gasps]

13:16.916 --> 13:17.916
Sorry, Paul.

13:19.041 --> 13:20.750
[growling, yelling]

13:21.875 --> 13:24.125
Roll out the red carpet.
Here's the super cops.

13:24.208 --> 13:26.375
- [heckling, shouting]
- Hey, what does the fox say?

13:26.458 --> 13:27.458
You suck! [laughing]

13:27.541 --> 13:28.750
Easy, partner.

13:28.833 --> 13:30.208
Let me ask you something.

13:30.291 --> 13:31.750
Do you think
we're a good team?

13:31.833 --> 13:33.208
Of course.

13:33.291 --> 13:34.458
I just...

13:34.541 --> 13:36.250
I just wish I knew
what we had to do

13:36.333 --> 13:38.166
to prove it to everyone else.

13:38.250 --> 13:41.250
Or maybe we don't have
to prove anything to anybody.

13:41.333 --> 13:42.250
[knocking]

13:42.333 --> 13:44.625
- [laughing continues]
- [Judy] Hmm.

13:44.708 --> 13:47.041
- We do. Forever.
- Oof!

13:47.125 --> 13:48.541
And the sooner
everyone sees

13:48.625 --> 13:50.541
a fox and a bunny can be
great partners, the better.

13:50.625 --> 13:52.416
Enjoy it. I got two.

13:52.500 --> 13:54.208
I'd rather chew off
my own arm.

13:54.291 --> 13:56.083
Happy anniversary!

13:57.583 --> 14:01.458
[♪ upbeat music playing]

14:03.875 --> 14:05.416
- [grunts, gasping] Coconut!
- [snarling]

14:05.500 --> 14:06.500
[Joel] Coconut!

14:15.916 --> 14:17.500
[stomping, rumbling]

14:19.041 --> 14:20.375
[trumpeting]

14:28.333 --> 14:30.458
- [rumbling]
- [elephants trumpeting]

14:30.541 --> 14:33.791
[Bonnie] <i>So, saw you on TV.</i>
<i>You okay?</i>

14:33.875 --> 14:35.375
Everything's fine, Mom.

14:35.458 --> 14:38.083
[Stu] <i>Uh-oh. Everyone knows</i>
<i>"fine" is a cry for help.</i>

14:38.166 --> 14:39.500
<i>You know who else</i>
<i>cried for help?</i>

14:39.583 --> 14:40.750
<i>That dik-dik</i>
<i>stuck in that tuba.</i>

14:40.833 --> 14:43.708
<i>Oh, him and the dik-dik. What</i>
<i>does your fox partner say?</i>

14:43.791 --> 14:47.708
[Judy] <i>Well, Nick's</i>
<i>not really a talker.</i>

14:48.291 --> 14:50.875
[Bonnie] <i>Well, you two</i>
<i>are very different.</i>

14:50.958 --> 14:53.208
<i>Small-town hero</i>
<i>raised on a farm.</i>

14:53.291 --> 14:55.083
<i>Big-city crook</i>
<i>raised on the streets.</i>

14:55.166 --> 14:56.166
<i>I pray every day</i>

14:56.250 --> 14:58.000
<i>that you'll come back home</i>
<i>and make babies.</i>

14:58.083 --> 14:59.125
[Bonnie] <i>Mom!</i>

14:59.208 --> 15:00.583
<i>Just remember the first rule</i>
<i>of partnerships.</i>

15:00.666 --> 15:02.583
<i>You can be right</i>
<i>or you can be happy.</i>

15:02.666 --> 15:03.500
<i>That's true.</i>

15:03.583 --> 15:05.250
[Stu] <i>There's nothing wrong</i>
<i>with dying a little inside</i>

15:05.333 --> 15:06.541
<i>so you can meet in the middle.</i>

15:06.625 --> 15:07.583
<i>Honey, you're pushing me out.</i>

15:07.666 --> 15:08.791
<i>I wanna make sure</i>
<i>I can be seen.</i>

15:08.875 --> 15:09.875
[Bonnie] <i>Well, if she</i>
<i>could see both of us.</i>

15:09.958 --> 15:11.541
- Gotta go. Work to do.
<i>- </i>[Bonnie] <i>Bye, bun-bun.</i>

15:11.625 --> 15:12.916
[Stu]
<i>Everything's gonna be fine.</i>

15:13.000 --> 15:14.500
<i>- You two just need a new case.</i>
- Got it. Love you.

15:14.583 --> 15:16.083
<i>Maybe try to find</i>
<i>that dik-dik.</i>

15:16.166 --> 15:17.000
Bye.

15:17.083 --> 15:18.458
[sighs]

15:25.791 --> 15:26.833
[sighs]

15:26.916 --> 15:29.750
- [♪ vocalizing theme music]
- [laughing]

15:29.833 --> 15:31.750
[audience] <i>Squeal of Fortune!</i>

15:31.833 --> 15:34.666
<i>Tomorrow's weather is,</i>
<i>again, everything.</i>

15:34.750 --> 15:35.791
[Purrrnacleo]
<i>...to announce that</i>

15:35.875 --> 15:38.083
<i>the long-awaited</i>
<i>Tundratown expansion</i>

15:38.166 --> 15:39.208
<i>will be starting soon.</i>

15:39.291 --> 15:41.166
<i>Residents continue</i>
<i>to raise concerns</i>

15:41.250 --> 15:43.041
<i>about the future</i>
<i>of their neighborhood.</i>

15:43.125 --> 15:46.916
[Howlett] <i>But tonight</i>
<i>we put our differences aside</i>

15:47.000 --> 15:48.833
<i>and celebrate</i>
<i>at the Zootennial gala,</i>

15:48.916 --> 15:51.375
<i>where the Lynxley Journal</i>
<i>will be on display</i>

15:51.458 --> 15:53.708
<i>for the first time</i>
<i>in a century,</i>

15:53.791 --> 15:56.291
<i>following an infamous</i>
<i>reptile attack.</i>

15:56.916 --> 15:58.208
<i>The Lynxley Journal,</i>

15:58.291 --> 16:00.291
<i>containing the patented</i>
<i>weather wall plans,</i>

16:00.375 --> 16:02.958
<i>was originally written by</i>
<i>Ebenezer Lynxley,</i>

16:03.041 --> 16:03.958
<i>bringing the whole...</i>

16:18.666 --> 16:20.333
Same catering company.

16:22.583 --> 16:23.791
Mmm.

16:33.250 --> 16:34.750
The Lynxley journal.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.375
<i>Truth bomb!</i>

16:44.458 --> 16:46.333
<i>The 100th anniversary</i>
<i>of the weather walls</i>

16:46.416 --> 16:48.833
<i>is also the 100th anniversary</i>

16:48.916 --> 16:51.333
<i>of Zootopia's</i>
<i>only snake attack.</i>

16:51.916 --> 16:53.958
<i>The victim? A tortoise.</i>

16:54.041 --> 16:56.916
<i>The Lynxley family maid</i>

16:57.000 --> 16:59.750
<i>who was fanged while stopping</i>
<i>a venomous snake</i>

16:59.833 --> 17:02.250
<i>from stealing</i>
<i>the Lynxley Journal.</i>

17:02.333 --> 17:04.958
<i>No one has seen a snake</i>
<i>in Zootopia since.</i>

17:05.041 --> 17:08.541
<i>But I'm convinced</i>
<i>one will return.</i>

17:08.625 --> 17:10.250
<i>My only question is,</i>

17:10.333 --> 17:15.458
<i>is he gonna be wearing</i>
<i>half-a-pants or one long sock?</i>

17:20.125 --> 17:23.125
- [villain groans]
<i>- You say, "Justice is dead."</i>

17:23.208 --> 17:25.333
<i>I say, "Neigh!"</i>

17:25.875 --> 17:26.708
<i>Ha-cha!</i>

17:27.291 --> 17:29.458
[Winddancer shouting]

17:29.541 --> 17:30.375
[villain groaning]

17:30.458 --> 17:32.083
Well, well,
you miss me already, huh?

17:32.166 --> 17:33.375
[Judy] <i>The stolen van</i>
<i>with the snake skin</i>

17:33.458 --> 17:34.791
<i>is from the same</i>
<i>catering company</i>

17:34.875 --> 17:36.250
<i>- that's working the gala.</i>
- Mm-hmm.

17:36.333 --> 17:38.666
This is you studying
your partner book?

17:38.750 --> 17:40.250
<i>Listen to me. Venomous snakes</i>

17:40.333 --> 17:42.333
<i>tried to steal</i>
<i>the Lynxleys's journal before.</i>

17:42.416 --> 17:44.208
<i>What if they're back in town</i>
<i>to steal it again?</i>

17:44.291 --> 17:45.750
- No snake has set foot...
- [knocking]

17:45.833 --> 17:48.458
...in Zootopia in forever,
okay?

17:48.541 --> 17:50.125
Even if they had feet.
[chuckles]

17:50.208 --> 17:51.500
Look, we're already
in the hot seat, Carrots,

17:51.583 --> 17:53.083
and pizza's here. Gotta go--

17:53.166 --> 17:54.208
If there's a fanging
at the gala

17:54.291 --> 17:55.416
and we do nothing to stop it,

17:55.500 --> 17:57.333
then we are not
doing our jobs...

17:57.416 --> 18:00.208
Yikes. No wonder
you never invite me over.

18:00.291 --> 18:01.791
Foxes are solitary.

18:01.875 --> 18:04.000
And, look, we go
and you're wrong,

18:04.083 --> 18:05.125
Chief Beef will split us up.

18:05.208 --> 18:06.250
And if we don't get a win soon

18:06.333 --> 18:07.625
and prove
we're great partners,

18:07.708 --> 18:09.625
the chief will
split us up anyway.

18:09.708 --> 18:11.166
Check the perimeter.
Snoop a little.

18:11.250 --> 18:13.000
We find nothing, we bail.

18:13.083 --> 18:14.208
But if I'm right,

18:14.291 --> 18:15.333
no one will question

18:15.416 --> 18:17.458
whether you and I
belong together again.

18:18.208 --> 18:19.375
We need this.

18:20.791 --> 18:21.833
Fine.

18:21.916 --> 18:24.375
But we'll still have
to get through security,

18:24.458 --> 18:25.916
and in fancy town,
a fox and a bunny

18:26.000 --> 18:28.291
won't exactly blend in. Oof!

18:28.375 --> 18:30.375
[Judy] That's why
we'll be undercover!

18:30.458 --> 18:31.500
[engine revving]

18:31.583 --> 18:33.791
[♪ upbeat pop music playing,
Shakira "Zoo"]

18:34.750 --> 18:36.708
See you're still
in the driver's seat. Whoa!

18:36.791 --> 18:39.000
[Gazelle singing]
♪ <i>Come on, get on up </i>♪

18:39.083 --> 18:41.041
♪ <i>We're wild</i>
<i>And we can't be tamed </i>♪

18:41.125 --> 18:44.125
♪ <i>And we're turning the floor</i>
<i>Into a zoo-ooh-ooh </i>♪

18:44.208 --> 18:45.041
Here we go!

18:45.125 --> 18:46.125
Here we go! Let's go!

18:47.625 --> 18:49.500
Zootopia, let me hear ya!

18:51.916 --> 18:55.666
♪ <i>We live in a crazy world</i>
<i>Caught up in a rat race </i>♪

18:55.750 --> 18:59.125
♪ <i>Concrete jungle life</i>
<i>Is sometimes a mad place </i>♪

18:59.208 --> 19:02.625
♪ <i>It's you and me together</i>
<i>At the end of a wild day </i>♪

19:02.708 --> 19:06.375
♪ <i>Don't keep it all bottled up</i>
<i>And release your energy </i>♪

19:08.041 --> 19:11.875
♪ <i>Only reason we are here</i>
<i>Is to celebrate </i>♪

19:11.958 --> 19:15.541
♪ <i>In a place where anyone</i>
<i>Can be anything </i>♪

19:15.625 --> 19:19.000
♪ <i>Hold on to this moment</i>
<i>Don't let it fade away </i>♪

19:19.083 --> 19:21.458
♪ <i>Baby</i>
<i>Keep the music playin'</i> ♪

19:21.541 --> 19:23.375
♪ <i>Come on, get on up </i>♪

19:23.458 --> 19:25.750
♪ <i>We're wild</i>
<i>And we can't be tamed </i>♪

19:25.833 --> 19:28.958
♪ <i>And we're turnin' the floor</i>
<i>Into a zoo-ooh-ooh </i>♪

19:29.041 --> 19:30.916
♪ <i>Come on, keep it up </i>♪

19:31.000 --> 19:33.208
♪ <i>It's fun if</i>
<i>You're down to play </i>♪

19:33.291 --> 19:36.125
♪ <i>And we're turnin' the floor</i>
<i>Into a zoo-ooh-ooh </i>♪

19:37.166 --> 19:38.625
[Clawhauser grunts]

19:39.250 --> 19:41.916
Ah, cats and lights.
I know better.

19:42.000 --> 19:43.791
♪ <i>A zoo-ooh-ooh </i>♪

19:43.875 --> 19:45.583
♪ <i>Come on, get on up </i>♪

19:45.666 --> 19:48.083
♪ <i>We're wild</i>
<i>And we can't be tamed </i>♪

19:48.166 --> 19:51.250
♪ <i>And we're turnin' the floor</i>
<i>Into a zoo-ooh-ooh </i>♪

19:51.333 --> 19:53.041
Mayor Winddancer
has arrived...

19:53.125 --> 19:53.958
Ha-cha!

19:54.041 --> 19:56.583
...star of the revenge
trilogy, <i>The Neigh-sayer</i>.

19:56.666 --> 19:58.166
No pictures, please.

19:58.250 --> 20:00.208
[laughs] Come on. It's me.

20:00.291 --> 20:02.666
And that, and that one,
and then this one.

20:02.750 --> 20:04.791
Mr. Lynxley,
when will you begin

20:04.875 --> 20:06.125
- the Tundratown expansion?
- Come on, Dad.

20:06.208 --> 20:08.666
Have a wonderful time
at the party.

20:08.750 --> 20:10.291
♪ <i>It's fun if</i>
<i>You're down to play</i> ♪

20:10.375 --> 20:13.625
♪ <i>And we're turning the floor</i>
<i>Into a zoo-ooh-ooh </i>♪

20:13.708 --> 20:15.375
[crowd cheering]

20:19.583 --> 20:21.708
- [fireworks banging]
- [crowd cheering]

20:23.583 --> 20:25.041
[yelps]

20:25.125 --> 20:26.125
D'oh.

20:30.000 --> 20:31.416
[Judy] No snow.

20:31.500 --> 20:32.500
Hmm.

20:32.583 --> 20:33.875
This one's warmer.

20:34.375 --> 20:37.375
A reptile in Tundratown might
need that to survive the cold.

20:39.750 --> 20:41.250
- [Nick] Oh, my God. A viper!
- [gasps]

20:41.791 --> 20:44.250
[German accent]
A "vindow viper." <i>Ja</i>.

20:44.333 --> 20:45.541
[chuckles, winces]

20:47.125 --> 20:48.041
[gasps]

20:48.958 --> 20:50.000
Back door ajar.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.083
[Nick] Anyone could have
left it like that.

20:52.166 --> 20:53.583
And you said,
"Snoop a little,"

20:53.666 --> 20:55.125
not break and enter-- Oh, God!

20:56.291 --> 20:57.958
Oh, we were always
going inside. Got it.

20:58.041 --> 20:59.583
Same page means your page.

20:59.666 --> 21:01.208
It's called a hustle,
sweetheart.

21:01.291 --> 21:02.833
You change out here.
I get the van.

21:13.625 --> 21:14.625
[van door opening]

21:16.166 --> 21:17.250
[sighs]

21:18.333 --> 21:19.375
[Nick] Huh.

21:19.875 --> 21:21.583
It's the Zootennial Gala.

21:21.666 --> 21:22.875
A bunny comes prepared.

21:24.208 --> 21:25.208
[Judy sighs]

21:25.791 --> 21:27.291
You know, I used to dream of

21:27.375 --> 21:28.958
infiltrating a place
like this.

21:30.583 --> 21:32.583
[♪ sentimental music playing]

21:35.833 --> 21:38.833
You know, this is not
your worst idea.

21:39.541 --> 21:41.458
Wow, that was almost
a compliment.

21:41.958 --> 21:43.875
Your worst idea is
what you did with your ears.

21:43.958 --> 21:44.958
[groans]

21:45.666 --> 21:46.666
All right.

21:48.375 --> 21:50.375
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

21:59.041 --> 22:01.375
[announcer] <i>Welcome to</i>
<i>the Zootennial Gala...</i>

22:01.458 --> 22:02.291
[grunts]

22:02.375 --> 22:05.875
<i>...featuring the original</i>
<i>Lynxley Journal.</i>

22:05.958 --> 22:09.916
Why would a snake wanna steal
some old book anyway?

22:10.000 --> 22:11.375
[Judy] I don't know.

22:11.458 --> 22:12.583
[mouse] Yeehaw!

22:12.666 --> 22:14.416
But no one is gonna steal it,

22:14.500 --> 22:16.208
because we are here
to protect it.

22:19.625 --> 22:22.916
[Judy] The journal is in
the reserved section. Okay.

22:23.500 --> 22:24.500
[Nick groans]

22:24.583 --> 22:25.583
Come on.

22:25.666 --> 22:26.666
Slow down.

22:26.750 --> 22:30.375
You want to fit in?
Commando is not gonna cut it.

22:30.458 --> 22:32.375
It's not just the clothes,
m'kay?

22:32.458 --> 22:34.000
It is the vibe.

22:34.083 --> 22:36.750
Good to see ya.
Hey, real nice humps.

22:36.833 --> 22:39.875
Oh, is that real mink?
This is real fox. [laughs]

22:39.958 --> 22:41.791
Get invited to a lot of these?

22:41.875 --> 22:44.041
Mmm. Invited? No.

22:44.125 --> 22:46.583
But there's other reasons
to hob knob.

22:47.208 --> 22:48.333
[gasps, stifles shout]

22:48.416 --> 22:50.708
Madam, excuse me.
Is this yours?

22:50.791 --> 22:52.208
Why, yes.

22:52.291 --> 22:54.958
- Well, allow me.
- [chuckles]

22:56.791 --> 22:58.375
Clever fox.

22:58.458 --> 22:59.458
Ooh, there!

23:00.375 --> 23:02.791
[chuckles] I don't think
it has enough guards.

23:03.416 --> 23:05.458
I'll get a closer look.
Watch my six.

23:09.208 --> 23:10.416
[groans]

23:11.458 --> 23:13.208
[Nick] Uh-oh. Bogo alert.

23:13.291 --> 23:14.291
Ah.

23:14.958 --> 23:16.041
[growls]

23:25.583 --> 23:26.875
Hmm.

23:26.958 --> 23:29.041
Cover's made of metal.

23:29.125 --> 23:31.666
[Nick on comms] <i>Gruffalo</i>
<i>Buffalo has joined the mix.</i>

23:31.750 --> 23:32.833
<i>Three o'clock.</i>

23:41.166 --> 23:43.750
- Oh! Excuse me. I am so sorry.
- Oh! Oh, no. Sorry.

23:43.833 --> 23:45.666
Here, lemme just... Oh, nope.

23:45.750 --> 23:48.708
That belongs to you.
I apologize. [chuckles]

23:48.791 --> 23:50.375
Oh, gosh. He hates me.

23:50.458 --> 23:51.291
Here.

23:51.375 --> 23:52.916
Ah! You're my hero.

23:53.000 --> 23:56.541
Well, just like to be prepared
for any possible scenario.

23:56.625 --> 23:59.208
Which is not a weird thing
to say at a party.

23:59.291 --> 24:01.791
Well, I just mopped a spill
with that guy's tail,

24:01.875 --> 24:03.125
so... [chuckles]

24:03.208 --> 24:04.208
Paw!

24:05.583 --> 24:08.500
Uh, Pawbert. I am Pawbert. Hi.

24:08.583 --> 24:10.041
Judy. I'm Judy Hopps.

24:10.125 --> 24:11.958
Argh! What the pork?

24:12.041 --> 24:14.041
Well, 'tis nice
to meet you, Judy...

24:14.125 --> 24:16.583
Wait. Judy Hopps?
The Judy Hopps?

24:16.666 --> 24:18.375
[laughs] Are you working this?

24:18.458 --> 24:20.625
I mean, you're clearly
working it. [chuckles]

24:20.708 --> 24:22.375
But are you actually
working this?

24:22.458 --> 24:24.666
[chuckles] Uh, no.
I'm actually...

24:24.750 --> 24:25.958
Well, it's just a hunch.

24:26.041 --> 24:27.458
...protecting that.

24:28.250 --> 24:30.375
Good. I don't think
it has enough guards.

24:30.458 --> 24:31.291
[both laugh]

24:31.375 --> 24:32.958
[Nick on comms]
<i>Uh, that was my joke.</i>

24:33.041 --> 24:34.583
Yeah, and there's
nothing here.

24:34.666 --> 24:36.250
Let's call it a night.

24:36.333 --> 24:37.333
Hopps?

24:42.041 --> 24:43.500
- [♪ fanfare playing]
- [guests applauding]

24:43.583 --> 24:44.708
Well, we should...

24:44.791 --> 24:45.833
It was nice to meet you.

24:45.916 --> 24:47.375
Yes, and you.

24:47.458 --> 24:48.666
Uh, bon appétit.

24:48.750 --> 24:50.791
If, at any point tonight,

24:50.875 --> 24:52.166
you choose to eat,
bon appétit then.

24:52.250 --> 24:53.083
[Cattrick clears throat]

24:53.166 --> 24:55.250
You're supposed to be
off stage, Pawbert.

24:55.333 --> 24:57.458
Yeah, get off stage, Pawbert.

24:57.541 --> 24:58.666
Wait, are you...

24:58.750 --> 25:01.291
Yeah, I am a Lynxley.

25:01.375 --> 25:02.875
Or, you know,
I'm trying to be.

25:02.958 --> 25:04.041
Now, Pawbert.

25:04.125 --> 25:05.208
Come on, Papi.

25:05.291 --> 25:06.375
I got you, Pa.
Don't you worry.

25:06.458 --> 25:07.625
No, I have him. I have him.

25:07.708 --> 25:10.208
[Winddancer] All right,
let's get this thing started.

25:10.291 --> 25:11.916
- [chuckling]
- [crowd cheering]

25:13.083 --> 25:13.916
Huh.

25:14.541 --> 25:16.750
[Winddancer] Welcome to
the Zootennial Gala.

25:16.833 --> 25:19.416
Hey, Hopps.
I think I might actually...

25:19.500 --> 25:20.666
I think I've got something.

25:21.291 --> 25:23.000
Ah. Look at you all.

25:23.083 --> 25:25.541
[laughing] Good to see ya.

25:25.625 --> 25:27.208
It is with great pleasure

25:27.291 --> 25:29.666
that I introduce the
third-generation visionary...

25:29.750 --> 25:32.083
Carrots, can you hear me?
I have a trail.

25:32.166 --> 25:33.125
[Winddancer]
...who has continued

25:33.208 --> 25:34.583
the legacy of our great city,

25:34.666 --> 25:36.500
Milton Lynxley.

25:36.583 --> 25:37.916
Thank you.

25:38.000 --> 25:39.333
- Thank you very much.
- Carrots. Carrots.

25:39.416 --> 25:40.416
[grunts]

25:41.458 --> 25:42.958
What are you doing here?

25:43.041 --> 25:44.041
Chief, she was right.

25:44.125 --> 25:45.250
- You're done.
- Wait. No, no.

25:45.333 --> 25:46.166
You're both done.

25:46.250 --> 25:48.000
My grandpa had a dream

25:48.083 --> 25:49.875
to build a city
for all animals.

25:49.958 --> 25:51.125
Nick?

25:51.708 --> 25:55.791
[Milton Lynxley]
To truly be better together.

25:55.875 --> 25:56.833
[gasps]

25:57.625 --> 25:59.625
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

26:06.458 --> 26:07.916
[high-pitched]
There's a snake!

26:08.000 --> 26:09.000
Snake, snake, snake!

26:09.666 --> 26:11.500
[Zebros] Go, bro, go.

26:11.583 --> 26:13.458
I will remember you, zebra.

26:13.541 --> 26:14.791
[gasps, whimpers]

26:22.416 --> 26:23.500
- [gasps]
- Ah!

26:23.583 --> 26:24.416
[yells]

26:25.125 --> 26:26.458
[elephant trumpeting]

26:28.708 --> 26:29.708
[Nick] Whoa!

26:33.916 --> 26:35.125
[muffled shout]

26:36.833 --> 26:38.000
Judy. Judy!

26:39.250 --> 26:40.250
[pig squeals]

26:43.291 --> 26:44.500
[gasps] I knew it!

26:47.958 --> 26:49.208
[Milton whimpering]

26:54.625 --> 26:56.958
- [snake panting]
- [Milton groaning]

27:02.875 --> 27:03.875
Stop!

27:03.958 --> 27:05.375
- [snake whimpers]
- [Judy grunts]

27:05.458 --> 27:07.791
Please.
You don't have to hurt him.

27:07.875 --> 27:09.041
[snake breathes shakily]

27:09.125 --> 27:10.125
Hurt him?

27:11.125 --> 27:15.041
Snakes never hurt anyone.

27:15.125 --> 27:17.000
We aren't the bad guys.

27:17.750 --> 27:19.000
They are.

27:20.250 --> 27:24.833
And this journal holds
the secret that will prove it.

27:25.541 --> 27:29.541
I have to prove it. Please.

27:31.666 --> 27:34.875
This is our only chance
to set things right.

27:35.375 --> 27:37.166
And when I do,

27:37.250 --> 27:41.625
my family will finally
be able to come home.

27:42.125 --> 27:42.958
- [frying pan clangs]
- [Nick] Woo!

27:43.041 --> 27:45.291
- Oh, no!
- [laughs] I am here.

27:45.375 --> 27:47.208
Hopps and Wilde... [chuckles]
...dream team.

27:47.750 --> 27:49.750
We got him. Or her.

27:49.833 --> 27:51.750
Reptiles, it's, like,
who knows? [chuckles]

27:53.458 --> 27:54.958
The cops are right behind us.

27:56.291 --> 27:57.750
Kill the snake.

27:57.833 --> 27:59.250
We'll burn the journal.

27:59.333 --> 28:01.708
If he wants it,
it's dangerous.

28:02.875 --> 28:07.291
And then you two will file
a report that he attacked us,

28:07.375 --> 28:11.000
and you will keep
your mouths shut.

28:13.625 --> 28:14.458
Step aside.

28:18.625 --> 28:20.083
Put out the fire!

28:21.250 --> 28:23.208
- Carrots, come on.
- Help me save him.

28:23.291 --> 28:24.625
- Carrots, we need--
- Nick.

28:25.250 --> 28:27.125
Cold! Cold!

28:27.208 --> 28:28.333
- [Kitty yells]
- [Milton groans]

28:29.791 --> 28:30.708
[snake wails]

28:30.791 --> 28:32.041
[grunts, groans]

28:34.291 --> 28:35.333
- [grunts]
- Chief.

28:35.416 --> 28:37.125
He'll be okay.

28:37.208 --> 28:39.333
Antivenom. He can be saved
with antivenom.

28:39.416 --> 28:41.875
Hopps, what did you do?

28:41.958 --> 28:43.625
- No, Hogg-- Hoggbottom.
- They're helping the snake.

28:43.708 --> 28:44.708
They're trying to kill
the chief!

28:44.791 --> 28:46.541
- Hoggbottom, no. Please.
- Backup! I need backup!

28:46.625 --> 28:48.208
- My page. Let's go.
- Wait, wait, wait.

28:48.291 --> 28:50.583
I need the journal
and probably a sweater.

28:50.666 --> 28:51.750
[shrieks]

28:51.833 --> 28:53.375
W-whoa.

28:53.458 --> 28:55.416
[gasps] Cold.

28:58.916 --> 29:00.333
- [Hoggbottom] On the ground.
- Wait.

29:01.541 --> 29:03.708
- [Hoggbottom] Oi!
- Next time, we stay home?

29:03.791 --> 29:05.125
[Hoggbottom] Don't you move.

29:05.208 --> 29:07.250
[panting, grunting]

29:09.000 --> 29:10.291
No. Stop them!

29:10.375 --> 29:11.375
- Oi!
- [Judy] Come on.

29:11.458 --> 29:12.833
- Stop!
- Come on!

29:12.916 --> 29:14.250
Stop!

29:14.791 --> 29:16.000
[Judy grunts]

29:16.583 --> 29:17.583
[yelps]

29:18.541 --> 29:20.833
[Judy on carrot pen]
<i>I really am just a dumb bunny.</i>

29:20.916 --> 29:23.041
Accident.
Your words, not mine.

29:23.125 --> 29:24.750
[both shriek]

29:30.166 --> 29:31.958
[Mr. Big grunts]

29:32.500 --> 29:34.500
Put 'em in the trunk.

29:34.583 --> 29:35.458
[both yelp]

29:36.041 --> 29:37.208
[both groan]

29:46.041 --> 29:48.375
[Purrrnacleo]
<i>"Ter-roar" in Tundratown.</i>

29:48.458 --> 29:50.250
[Nutriamo]
<i>A fanging at the fiesta.</i>

29:50.333 --> 29:52.416
A howl-a at the gala

29:52.500 --> 29:54.708
as a venomous snake
attacks the founding family.

29:54.791 --> 29:56.708
[Howlett] <i>More shocking,</i>
<i>the snake was aided</i>

29:56.791 --> 30:00.208
<i>by embattled ZPD officers</i>
<i>Nicholas Wilde and Judy Hopps.</i>

30:00.291 --> 30:02.750
All three now suspects
in the tragic fanging

30:02.833 --> 30:04.541
<i>of Zootopia's chief of police</i>

30:04.625 --> 30:07.125
<i>and considered</i>
<i>extremely dangerous.</i>

30:08.083 --> 30:09.458
Chief Bogo...

30:10.583 --> 30:11.416
is dead.

30:11.500 --> 30:12.833
[crowd gasps]

30:13.458 --> 30:15.500
Those are words I'm glad
I don't have to say.

30:15.583 --> 30:16.458
[crowd exhales deeply]

30:16.541 --> 30:17.541
I might have to soon.

30:17.625 --> 30:19.625
The doctors
are a little weirded out, but

30:19.708 --> 30:24.333
what has happened tonight
was more than horseplay.

30:27.375 --> 30:28.916
[Milton] Hmm.

30:29.000 --> 30:30.791
Uh, we, uh...

30:30.875 --> 30:33.208
We're gonna take
that snake down.

30:33.291 --> 30:36.250
And the fox and that rabbit!

30:37.541 --> 30:40.791
Do you know how many mayors
they've already destroyed?

30:42.958 --> 30:47.375
One, two... I got up to two.

30:47.458 --> 30:49.625
Would you like to be "three"?

30:50.541 --> 30:53.041
I want them gone.

30:53.708 --> 30:57.125
But aren't there... laws?

30:57.958 --> 31:01.958
I will say this once, Brian.

31:02.500 --> 31:07.458
You will retrieve the journal
and bury them.

31:08.541 --> 31:09.375
Or maybe

31:09.458 --> 31:12.083
- I chose the wrong mayor.
- [Winddancer gulps]

31:14.041 --> 31:16.875
Did I choose the wrong mayor?

31:17.541 --> 31:18.583
[gulps]

31:22.125 --> 31:24.041
[sirens wailing]

31:35.208 --> 31:37.291
- [phone ringing]
- [Judy straining]

31:46.250 --> 31:47.458
Hmm.

31:49.291 --> 31:50.791
[phone chimes]

32:00.583 --> 32:02.208
[sighs]

32:06.875 --> 32:07.708
Hey.

32:07.791 --> 32:10.500
The phone is the first thing
they'll track.

32:10.583 --> 32:11.416
[Judy gasps]

32:11.500 --> 32:17.416
Sorry. I have never been on
the run from the law before.

32:17.500 --> 32:18.750
Yeah. Boy.

32:18.833 --> 32:21.791
It's almost like we shouldn't
have gone to that gala, huh?

32:22.541 --> 32:24.291
Okie doke.
We already did it your way.

32:24.375 --> 32:26.625
With Mr. Big, we do it mine.

32:26.708 --> 32:29.291
This is where having
a partner from the underworld

32:29.375 --> 32:30.708
is really gonna pay off.

32:31.750 --> 32:34.000
Raymond! And is that Kev...

32:38.625 --> 32:41.083
[♪ jazz music playing]

32:57.666 --> 33:00.333
Welcome to my warehouse.

33:00.416 --> 33:01.875
Oh, my God, I love your dress.

33:01.958 --> 33:03.958
Oh! Thank you.

33:04.041 --> 33:05.333
[grunts] Fru Fru and I

33:05.416 --> 33:08.333
are now equal partners
in the family business.

33:08.833 --> 33:12.916
She brings wonderful ideas
for crime and for fashion

33:13.000 --> 33:17.416
while I get more time to focus
on what matters most:

33:17.500 --> 33:20.291
being grandpapa
to my little Judith.

33:20.375 --> 33:22.041
Kiss my ring.

33:22.125 --> 33:23.041
[chuckles]

33:23.125 --> 33:24.166
Kiss the stinkin' ring
right now!

33:24.250 --> 33:25.291
You kiss it right now!
Kiss it!

33:25.833 --> 33:27.166
Mwah.

33:27.250 --> 33:28.875
<i>Nonno</i>, you said we were gonna

33:28.958 --> 33:31.375
make cement shoes
for Mr. Weaselton.

33:31.458 --> 33:33.333
Oh, that's my girl.

33:33.416 --> 33:35.041
They grow up so fast.

33:35.125 --> 33:37.250
- You shut your mouth, fox!
- You run your mouth too much!

33:38.208 --> 33:40.250
Anyways, you're in trouble.

33:40.333 --> 33:43.958
And we like one of yas,
so we're here to help.

33:44.041 --> 33:46.500
New clothes. New identities.

33:46.583 --> 33:48.500
Truck out of town
leaves in an hour.

33:48.583 --> 33:50.708
And your meter maid cart
is taken care of.

33:53.166 --> 33:54.291
[inhales]

33:54.375 --> 33:56.125
I think you misunderstand.

33:56.208 --> 33:58.333
We've been framed
by the lynxes.

33:58.416 --> 33:59.583
And an innocent snake needs...

33:59.666 --> 34:01.916
Judy, the lynxes
are killers...

34:02.000 --> 34:05.125
[grunts]
...and they have no honor.

34:05.208 --> 34:07.333
And this Tundratown expansion

34:07.416 --> 34:09.708
only makes them
more dangerous.

34:09.791 --> 34:14.041
Territorial animals will do
anything for more land.

34:14.125 --> 34:15.833
So, if whatever
you're tangled up in

34:15.916 --> 34:19.291
threatens their plans,
you're dead.

34:19.375 --> 34:22.708
You don't fight the cats.
You leave.

34:22.791 --> 34:25.875
Sir, I know you're trying
to look out for us.

34:25.958 --> 34:28.625
But we took an oath
to protect this city.

34:28.708 --> 34:30.416
And justice doesn't run.

34:30.500 --> 34:31.916
On behalf of myself,

34:32.000 --> 34:36.208
"Rick Wilde,"
and "Miss Trudy Cabbagepatch,"

34:36.291 --> 34:38.458
we thank you for your truck
to salvation and-- Ow!

34:38.541 --> 34:39.625
We cannot accept your offer.

34:39.708 --> 34:41.375
We are helping that snake.

34:41.458 --> 34:43.083
Boy, you're really
tossing that "we" around.

34:43.166 --> 34:44.458
Snakes may have been framed

34:44.541 --> 34:45.791
for the fanging
of that tortoise.

34:45.875 --> 34:47.541
Do you have any idea why?

34:47.625 --> 34:50.000
Or how this book
could prove it?

34:50.083 --> 34:51.583
I wish I did.

34:52.125 --> 34:54.333
But if it has to do
with snakes,

34:54.416 --> 34:57.416
your best bet
is talking to a reptile.

34:58.166 --> 34:59.791
Do you know any?

35:00.375 --> 35:01.958
Almost no one does.

35:02.041 --> 35:06.166
They keep to themselves,
hide out in Marsh Market.

35:06.250 --> 35:08.083
But you can still find 'em.

35:08.166 --> 35:10.583
You just need
a reptile expert.

35:10.666 --> 35:13.125
Someone local
who knows where to go.

35:13.208 --> 35:15.125
Lucky for you, I met someone.

35:15.208 --> 35:17.000
She runs a podcast!

35:17.583 --> 35:19.166
[Nick] No, no.
Trudy Cabbagepatch,

35:19.250 --> 35:21.291
Rick Wilde says no.

35:22.291 --> 35:24.166
[Nibbles] Oh, yeah!

35:25.416 --> 35:27.458
If Hopps and Wilde
are on the lam,

35:27.541 --> 35:30.333
subtle sleuthin' 'tis my jam.

35:30.416 --> 35:32.291
Woo! Mind the splinters.

35:32.375 --> 35:33.916
Oh, you called
the right beaver.

35:34.000 --> 35:37.041
If you wanna talk to
a reptile, I am your gal.

35:37.125 --> 35:38.833
Also, if you need to talk
to a jackalope,

35:38.916 --> 35:41.708
which are real, Mom!

35:41.791 --> 35:44.208
[chuckles]
Excuse us. Team meeting.

35:44.291 --> 35:45.791
Vetoing the beave.

35:45.875 --> 35:48.333
New vote: All in favor
of "Truck to Being Alive

35:48.416 --> 35:51.125
and Laying Low Till This
Blows Over-ville"? I mean...

35:51.208 --> 35:53.125
Hopps and Wilde
do not bail on a case.

35:53.208 --> 35:54.291
But she's crazy.

35:54.375 --> 35:56.833
Probably lead poisoning
from eating too many pencils.

35:59.666 --> 36:00.791
Do you know a reptile who can

36:00.875 --> 36:02.041
tell us the hidden secret
in here,

36:02.125 --> 36:03.791
or why the lynxes
framed the snakes?

36:04.416 --> 36:05.583
[sighs]

36:05.666 --> 36:07.833
Twenty-four hours.
Sunrise tomorrow.

36:07.916 --> 36:09.875
If we strike out,
then we go into hiding,

36:09.958 --> 36:11.333
and "Judy Cabbagepatch" it is.

36:11.416 --> 36:12.250
[horn honks]

36:12.750 --> 36:13.750
[groans]

36:13.833 --> 36:15.583
It's "Trudy" Cabbagepatch,

36:15.666 --> 36:17.083
and the safe word
is "coconut."

36:17.166 --> 36:19.458
In the darkness
of a dank underpass,

36:19.541 --> 36:20.958
they stepped into the vehicle,

36:21.041 --> 36:24.500
not realizing their lives
were about to change.

36:24.583 --> 36:26.750
Because we're gonna
meet a reptile?

36:26.833 --> 36:28.916
Because you're about to be
best buds

36:29.000 --> 36:31.875
with Nibbles Maplestick!

36:31.958 --> 36:35.541
Takes two to tango, but
a threesome to be somethin'.

36:35.625 --> 36:39.041
Let's find you a reptile
and romp the swamp.

36:46.541 --> 36:47.416
[inhales]

36:47.500 --> 36:49.250
Breathe it in!

36:49.333 --> 36:50.750
- [Judy] Oh!
- [Nibbles whoops]

36:54.416 --> 36:56.041
[Nibbles] Now, if any reptile
would know

36:56.125 --> 36:58.291
the secret of that book
and why the snake wants it...

36:58.375 --> 37:00.250
- Hey, Johnny!
- [Johnny] Oh, no!

37:00.333 --> 37:02.750
...it's my old lizard friend,
Jesús.

37:02.833 --> 37:05.916
[Judy] Why would a lizard
hide here?

37:07.708 --> 37:09.625
Well, when Zootopia
was founded,

37:09.708 --> 37:11.625
the whole neighborhood
got cut off

37:11.708 --> 37:13.000
from the rest of the town.

37:13.083 --> 37:14.458
Kinda on our own here.

37:14.541 --> 37:15.375
[grunting]

37:15.458 --> 37:17.625
Yeah, that's probably why
reptiles like it.

37:17.708 --> 37:19.375
They can just do their thing.

37:19.458 --> 37:20.833
Plus, it's the only place
in town

37:20.916 --> 37:23.875
you can get away with
wearing a shirt and no pants.

37:23.958 --> 37:25.958
Loving tour time
with Woodchuckles.

37:26.041 --> 37:27.458
- [whispers] Great call.
- [Judy growls]

37:27.541 --> 37:29.083
- We need her.
- Oh, yeah.

37:29.166 --> 37:30.166
Like a hole in the head.

37:30.250 --> 37:31.166
[dolphin squawks]

37:31.250 --> 37:32.916
Bad timing. Hmm.

37:33.541 --> 37:35.750
Okay, to get to
Jesús's hideout,

37:35.833 --> 37:37.333
we gotta take a ferry.

37:37.416 --> 37:38.750
Just let me handle the locals.

37:38.833 --> 37:41.583
Water folk tend to be a little
standoffish around landies.

37:41.666 --> 37:44.083
Well, I've been hustling
the streets since I was 12.

37:44.166 --> 37:46.375
I think I can handle
a juggling seal.

37:46.458 --> 37:48.375
- [roars]
- Oh! [chuckles]

37:48.458 --> 37:50.291
Sea lion.

37:50.375 --> 37:51.458
He's not from around here.

37:51.541 --> 37:53.000
- But coin's a coin.
- [growling]

37:53.083 --> 37:56.833
Oh, no. Change... [grunts]
...is a choking hazard.

37:56.916 --> 37:59.583
- Well, honest mistake.
- [roars]

37:59.666 --> 38:01.583
Do not do that!

38:01.666 --> 38:03.208
Let's let Nibbles handle this.

38:03.291 --> 38:04.791
[Nibbles] Thank you, Judith.

38:04.875 --> 38:07.416
Conversing with these
beautiful sea creatures

38:07.500 --> 38:09.416
is like talking to anyone
a little different.

38:09.500 --> 38:13.041
Just takes open
and respectful communication.

38:14.250 --> 38:15.583
[ringing]

38:15.666 --> 38:16.666
[bubbling]

38:21.708 --> 38:22.708
- Heya, bub.
- Hey, bub.

38:22.791 --> 38:24.083
- Heya, bub, hey.
- Hey, bub, heya.

38:24.166 --> 38:25.333
- Bubba, bubba, bubba.
- Bubba, bubba, bubba.

38:25.416 --> 38:27.333
- Heya, bub.
- Hey, bub. Hey, bub, bub.

38:27.416 --> 38:29.500
- Heya, bub. Bubby, bub.
- Hey, bub. Hey, bub. Hey, ho.

38:29.583 --> 38:30.500
- Heya, bub, bub.
- Hey, bub.

38:31.541 --> 38:32.583
Seen Jesús?

38:32.666 --> 38:33.666
Yup.

38:40.125 --> 38:41.916
And now we leave town.

38:42.000 --> 38:43.000
- [rumbling]
- [Judy yelps]

38:47.916 --> 38:49.083
[double whistle]

38:49.166 --> 38:50.166
Eh?

38:57.750 --> 38:59.333
Thank you for this.

39:00.083 --> 39:01.333
Happy anniversary.

39:01.416 --> 39:02.416
Oh.

39:02.500 --> 39:03.875
It's your anniversary?

39:05.250 --> 39:08.166
[George Givot]
♪ <i>This is the night </i>♪

39:08.250 --> 39:11.250
♪ <i>It's a beautiful night </i>♪

39:11.333 --> 39:17.041
- ♪ <i>And we call it bella notte </i>♪
- [Russ sings along]

39:21.500 --> 39:22.791
[sniffs]

39:23.708 --> 39:25.625
How are we gonna
find them now?

39:25.708 --> 39:26.708
[sea lion grunts]

39:27.708 --> 39:28.708
[growls]

39:30.750 --> 39:32.625
- [coin clinking]
- Thanks, seal.

39:32.708 --> 39:34.000
- [snarling]
- [Truffler shouts]

39:34.541 --> 39:36.583
Friend. No, no, no!

39:36.666 --> 39:37.875
I'm sorry. I'm sorry!

39:37.958 --> 39:39.458
[Truffler shouts]

39:40.208 --> 39:41.875
[Nibbles]
Just a little farther.

39:41.958 --> 39:44.500
Jesús and all the answers
you'll ever need

39:44.583 --> 39:46.000
are, uh, right here

39:46.083 --> 39:48.958
at the end of this
very scary, dark hallway.

39:49.041 --> 39:50.875
Boy, this is so much better

39:50.958 --> 39:52.916
than sitting on a beach
on Outback Island,

39:53.000 --> 39:55.041
sipping piña koalas.

39:55.125 --> 39:57.708
Hmm. We are not skipping town

39:57.791 --> 40:01.000
when there is an innocent
snake out there who needs us.

40:01.083 --> 40:03.791
He's got help:
his motorcycle buddy.

40:03.875 --> 40:04.958
Ah! [pants]

40:05.541 --> 40:08.208
You are acting weird.
What is your problem?

40:08.291 --> 40:10.375
Well, A, you railroaded me.

40:10.458 --> 40:12.083
And B... [inhales]

40:12.166 --> 40:13.666
...if you must know,

40:13.750 --> 40:18.041
I have an aversion
to reptiles.

40:18.125 --> 40:19.958
[chuckling] What?

40:20.041 --> 40:23.875
Oh, is my discomfort
hilarious to you?

40:23.958 --> 40:26.666
No, you're... I'm sorry.
You're right, we are partners.

40:26.750 --> 40:28.125
And whenever
I'm uncomfortable,

40:28.208 --> 40:30.625
you are always very
considerate of my feelings.

40:30.708 --> 40:31.541
Look out! Snake skin!

40:31.625 --> 40:32.583
- [Judy laughs]
- [Nick growls]

40:32.666 --> 40:33.666
- Ow!
- I'm slipping!

40:33.750 --> 40:34.666
I'm slipping! Hold the rail!

40:34.750 --> 40:36.083
- I'm holding the rail.
- Hold it. Hold it.

40:36.166 --> 40:37.250
- Stop pulling my ears!
- Hold the rail.

40:37.333 --> 40:38.166
Never pull a bunny's ears!

40:38.250 --> 40:40.041
- Hold the rail.
- Never pull a bunny's ears!

40:40.125 --> 40:41.625
[creaking]

40:42.958 --> 40:44.875
I think the real mystery

40:45.500 --> 40:47.500
is how you two
ever solved anything.

40:47.583 --> 40:49.125
[laughs]

40:49.208 --> 40:51.750
Anyhoo, let's see what Jesús
has to say about your journal.

40:51.833 --> 40:54.333
Oh, and if he offers you food,
accept.

40:55.375 --> 40:57.208
Declining is a sign
of disrespect,

40:57.291 --> 40:58.458
to all of them.

40:58.541 --> 41:00.041
"All of them"?

41:00.125 --> 41:01.416
[door rumbles]

41:01.500 --> 41:03.583
[♪ banjo music playing]

41:04.291 --> 41:05.416
[chatter, laughter]

41:10.708 --> 41:12.208
- [shudders]
- Ha! [laughs]

41:13.500 --> 41:14.583
[groans]

41:16.000 --> 41:17.875
[playing jazz]

41:24.041 --> 41:25.041
Order up.

41:26.541 --> 41:28.000
Hey, another drink.

41:28.500 --> 41:29.500
[belches]

41:31.000 --> 41:32.000
[whimpers]

41:34.541 --> 41:35.875
So warm.

41:36.375 --> 41:37.333
- Gah!
- [gecko shouts]

41:37.416 --> 41:38.250
[crunch]

41:38.916 --> 41:40.291
Whoops.

41:40.375 --> 41:41.375
No!

41:42.625 --> 41:44.791
[chuckles] Keep it.

41:46.166 --> 41:47.166
[shudders]

41:48.791 --> 41:51.000
[Nibbles] Jesús!

41:51.083 --> 41:52.666
Allow me to introduce
my friends.

41:52.750 --> 41:54.541
This is Judith and Nicholas.

41:54.625 --> 41:56.000
They are wanted fugitives

41:56.083 --> 41:57.416
investigating a snake mystery

41:57.500 --> 41:58.791
and trying
not to get murdered.

41:58.875 --> 42:00.208
May we sit?

42:03.666 --> 42:04.666
- [snapping]
- Oh. Okay.

42:05.208 --> 42:06.833
[all straining]

42:08.791 --> 42:10.125
[Judy squeals]

42:11.583 --> 42:13.791
Oh, I'm good,
but these guys look hungry.

42:18.083 --> 42:19.500
Thank you for meeting with us.

42:19.583 --> 42:22.833
We believe snakes were framed
for something in this journal,

42:22.916 --> 42:26.625
- perhaps pertaining to...
- Eat first, talk second.

42:27.166 --> 42:28.000
Oh.

42:29.291 --> 42:30.958
[Judy, Nick groan]

42:42.791 --> 42:44.125
- [whimpers]
- [gags]

42:50.250 --> 42:51.458
[shudders]

42:52.916 --> 42:53.916
Uh...

42:56.000 --> 42:57.291
[slurping]

42:57.375 --> 42:59.166
[gags]

43:03.666 --> 43:05.666
Hey, guys. They ate it!

43:05.750 --> 43:07.083
- [Jesús laughing]
- [all cheering]

43:07.166 --> 43:08.791
[Jesús] Look at their faces.
[laughs]

43:08.875 --> 43:10.333
I don't eat grubs.

43:10.416 --> 43:12.416
<i>Hermano</i>, get me a scone!

43:12.500 --> 43:14.000
[Jesús laughs]

43:14.083 --> 43:15.375
Okay, okay.

43:16.458 --> 43:17.541
Hmm.

43:18.333 --> 43:19.791
Metal cover.

43:20.750 --> 43:22.500
And what does that mean?

43:22.583 --> 43:23.583
It means

43:24.916 --> 43:25.958
it's fancy.

43:27.083 --> 43:30.041
It also means
the secret you're looking for

43:30.125 --> 43:32.083
is probably
right on the cover.

43:32.666 --> 43:35.583
Somehow vipers can see things
in the metal,

43:35.666 --> 43:37.583
even under the paint.

43:38.500 --> 43:40.791
This is Ebenezer Lynxley's
original journal

43:40.875 --> 43:42.041
for the weather walls.

43:42.125 --> 43:45.833
Why would he hide a secret
for a snake?

43:45.916 --> 43:47.083
I don't know.

43:47.166 --> 43:51.166
But it must have been big,
'cause a tortoise died for it.

43:51.666 --> 43:54.958
I am guessing
that it was a slow death.

43:55.791 --> 43:57.250
[sighs]

43:57.333 --> 43:58.333
[Nibbles groans]

43:58.416 --> 44:02.041
The fanging didn't just change
how folks saw snakes.

44:02.791 --> 44:05.666
No mammals trusted
any reptile after that.

44:07.375 --> 44:10.083
[Jesús]
That's why we all left.

44:10.166 --> 44:11.583
And that's when the Lynxleys

44:11.666 --> 44:14.416
expanded Tundratown
the first time.

44:15.875 --> 44:17.958
And it's happening again.

44:19.166 --> 44:21.333
The expansion is going here.

44:21.416 --> 44:24.916
[inhales] Marsh Market
will be buried in snow.

44:26.041 --> 44:27.666
We'll all get pushed out.

44:28.625 --> 44:30.833
Those lynxes
will get more land,

44:31.541 --> 44:34.208
and there's no way
to stop 'em.

44:40.041 --> 44:43.458
What if the secret
hidden in here could?

44:44.458 --> 44:45.916
Then I would say

44:46.000 --> 44:50.833
holding it puts the two of you
in grave danger.

44:50.916 --> 44:52.083
- [rumbling]
- [both gasp]

44:53.166 --> 44:54.500
- [rumbling grows louder]
- Ooh.

44:57.916 --> 44:59.583
- [all yelp]
- They tracked you?

44:59.666 --> 45:01.250
Hmm-hmm-hmm.

45:02.083 --> 45:03.083
Whoops.

45:03.166 --> 45:05.000
- [grunting]
- [all screaming]

45:05.083 --> 45:07.166
- It's the ZPD!
- [Lizard yelps]

45:07.250 --> 45:09.791
[slowly] Run!

45:09.875 --> 45:11.208
Leave the tails!

45:11.291 --> 45:12.791
Follow me. Come on!

45:15.500 --> 45:17.583
Wait. Why are you helping us?

45:17.666 --> 45:19.708
You two saved the city once.

45:19.791 --> 45:21.958
I reckon you can
save it again.

45:22.041 --> 45:23.833
And when you do,

45:23.916 --> 45:27.416
maybe everyone will see
we ain't that different.

45:28.625 --> 45:30.416
[jabbering]

45:31.958 --> 45:32.875
Huh.

45:33.541 --> 45:35.416
- Freeze!
- Yeah, freeze!

45:36.458 --> 45:37.458
I'm really sorry. But this is

45:37.541 --> 45:39.250
my family's only chance
to come home.

45:39.333 --> 45:40.500
Wait. We wanna help.

45:40.583 --> 45:41.916
Wait. Wait.

45:43.208 --> 45:44.875
Come back!

45:44.958 --> 45:46.833
There's no path.
Take the docks!

45:46.916 --> 45:48.000
Wha-- Carrots!

45:48.083 --> 45:49.875
Wait! We believe you!

45:49.958 --> 45:51.333
Nick! Come on! Come on!

45:51.416 --> 45:52.250
[sighs]

45:52.333 --> 45:53.375
- [thud]
- [Nick yelps]

45:58.250 --> 45:59.458
[Nick blabbering]

45:59.541 --> 46:00.583
- [thud]
- Ow!

46:03.000 --> 46:04.000
Grab it!

46:09.291 --> 46:10.291
Hey!

46:11.083 --> 46:13.500
I got eyes on them.
They're heading for the tubes!

46:13.583 --> 46:14.750
In pursuit.

46:18.916 --> 46:20.875
[Nick grunting]

46:23.750 --> 46:24.958
[shouting]

46:29.625 --> 46:30.750
[bells ring]

46:31.708 --> 46:32.541
Hey, bubba.

46:32.625 --> 46:33.583
- Hey, bub.
- Hey, bub.

46:33.666 --> 46:34.500
- Hey, bub.
- Hey, bub.

46:35.083 --> 46:35.916
Go!

46:36.875 --> 46:37.750
- Hey, bub.
- Hey, bub.

46:37.833 --> 46:38.666
- Bub-bye.
- Hey, Bub.

46:38.750 --> 46:39.583
- Bub-bye.
- Bub-bye.

46:39.666 --> 46:40.875
Bub-bye. Bye.

46:40.958 --> 46:42.250
- Hey, bub.
- Bub-bye.

46:44.833 --> 46:46.500
- [Nick shouts]
- [Nibbles whoops]

46:49.583 --> 46:52.333
Pro tip! If he goes
for the red line,

46:52.416 --> 46:54.250
do not follow!

46:54.333 --> 46:56.708
You will run out of air!

46:56.791 --> 46:58.833
Good luck! I love you!

46:59.625 --> 47:01.333
[onlookers gasping]

47:03.333 --> 47:04.333
Sorry.

47:04.958 --> 47:05.791
[Gary gulps]

47:05.875 --> 47:07.458
Cannonball!

47:10.333 --> 47:11.666
That's a red line. Red line!

47:11.750 --> 47:14.166
You're going to run out
of air! Coconut! Coconut!

47:16.708 --> 47:18.291
[muffled screams]

47:34.750 --> 47:36.833
[Duke Weaselton]
Anything you need, I got 'em.

47:36.916 --> 47:38.708
Sequels, prequels, requels.

47:38.791 --> 47:40.625
Who says the industry's
going down the tubes?

47:40.708 --> 47:42.208
[Nick yelling]

47:49.166 --> 47:50.458
[muffled dialogue]

48:24.541 --> 48:25.541
[Judy screaming]

48:26.375 --> 48:28.041
[both panting]

48:28.125 --> 48:29.958
[water spouting]

48:33.541 --> 48:34.583
Are you okay?

48:34.666 --> 48:36.500
Yeah. Yes.

48:37.125 --> 48:38.291
Uh, you?

48:38.375 --> 48:40.500
I... Well, I've...

48:40.583 --> 48:42.708
[stutters] I feel like some...

48:42.791 --> 48:45.416
some "sorries," uh,
may be in order.

48:46.166 --> 48:47.916
Nick, it's okay.

48:48.666 --> 48:51.291
I know you didn't want to
lose him on purpose.

48:52.166 --> 48:55.125
Oh, not me sorry. No, no.

48:55.208 --> 48:56.333
You sorry.

48:57.458 --> 49:00.791
Well, now we kinda have
no way to find him

49:00.875 --> 49:02.041
or stop the lynxes,

49:02.125 --> 49:04.000
so agree to disagree.

49:05.166 --> 49:06.291
But...

49:06.375 --> 49:07.791
we are alive.

49:07.875 --> 49:10.291
So if we can't find him,
that's great.

49:10.375 --> 49:13.208
What we can find
is a truck out of here.

49:13.291 --> 49:14.333
Gah.

49:27.500 --> 49:30.166
Box of old matches. Helpful.

49:30.250 --> 49:34.166
Trudy Cabbagepatch,
leaving town. We're done.

49:34.750 --> 49:36.125
Yodelayheehoo!

49:36.708 --> 49:38.833
Ah, dis is veird place
for you to be.

49:38.916 --> 49:40.125
<i>Ja</i>, very veird.

49:40.208 --> 49:41.916
Ach, zey fell out of ze tube.

49:42.000 --> 49:43.833
Okay, ve vill call police
to help!

49:43.916 --> 49:45.458
Nope! No, no, we're fine.

49:45.541 --> 49:47.625
Yep, we were
just leaving town.

49:47.708 --> 49:50.875
Actually, um,
do you happen to know

49:50.958 --> 49:52.875
where this tube goes?

49:52.958 --> 49:54.583
- Oh, Copenhoofen.
- [Jürgen] <i>Ja, ist Copenhoofen.</i>

49:54.666 --> 49:56.041
- Got it. Thank y--
- [Jürgen coughing]

49:56.125 --> 49:59.375
Oh, you chew too much.
This is not okay!

49:59.458 --> 50:01.166
[Jürgen coughing]

50:03.291 --> 50:04.541
Huh.

50:04.625 --> 50:06.833
Where did... Where did
you find these flowers?

50:06.916 --> 50:08.125
Oh, the Liebenflower?

50:08.208 --> 50:09.750
Ze tippity-top of ze mountain.

50:09.833 --> 50:11.083
Uh, zis is ze only place
zey grow.

50:11.166 --> 50:12.458
Oh, boy.

50:12.541 --> 50:13.833
- Is...
- [hooves clacking]

50:13.916 --> 50:17.375
Uh, is there anything else
up there?

50:17.458 --> 50:19.208
- Nope, there sure isn't.
- [Berthold] Oh,<i> ja.</i>

50:19.291 --> 50:20.625
Old Honeymoon Lodge.

50:20.708 --> 50:23.458
But is closed for long time.
Was hideout for snakes.

50:23.541 --> 50:24.541
[gasps]

50:25.708 --> 50:27.250
Honeymoon Lodge.

50:27.333 --> 50:28.666
- How...
- [hooves clacking]

50:28.750 --> 50:29.791
How do you reach it?

50:29.875 --> 50:32.708
Oh, tourists take ze tram
from Copenhoofen,

50:32.791 --> 50:34.916
but ze rope is faster.

50:35.916 --> 50:38.791
[Jürgen] Good luck! Have fun
at ze Honeymoon Lodge!

50:38.875 --> 50:39.875
Thank you!

50:43.833 --> 50:44.916
[Judy grunts]

50:46.291 --> 50:47.916
[Judy] What does the secret

50:48.000 --> 50:50.083
have to do with
the reptiles leaving town?

50:52.041 --> 50:54.041
How did it get hidden in the
journal in the first place?

50:54.125 --> 50:55.833
Will you slow down?

50:58.166 --> 50:59.375
How long do you think
it's going to be

50:59.458 --> 51:01.833
before Hoggbottom and the ZPD
figure out where we are?

51:01.916 --> 51:04.750
If anything,
we should be going faster.

51:05.958 --> 51:07.208
As I always say...

51:07.291 --> 51:10.500
[through carrot pen]
<i>I really am just a dumb bunny.</i>

51:10.583 --> 51:11.416
Nick...

51:11.500 --> 51:12.375
[rewinding]

51:12.458 --> 51:14.166
<i>I-- I-- I-- I-- I really am</i>

51:14.250 --> 51:16.041
<i>ju-- dumb-- dumb-- dumb--</i>
<i>dumb-- dumb-- dumb bunny.</i>

51:16.125 --> 51:18.291
<i>Just dumb-- dumb-- dumb--</i>
<i>dumb-- dumb-- dumb bunny.</i>

51:18.375 --> 51:21.708
This was a gift
to symbolize our partnership,

51:21.791 --> 51:24.166
and it is not appropriate
for this moment.

51:24.250 --> 51:25.791
Oh, no, I was just...
[chuckles]

51:25.875 --> 51:27.500
...hoping to jot down
some ideas

51:27.583 --> 51:29.708
for what we will put
on our tombstones.

51:29.791 --> 51:32.583
I'll start.
"His partner did it."

51:32.666 --> 51:33.500
What happened to you

51:33.583 --> 51:35.291
that you can't just have
a normal conversation?

51:36.500 --> 51:39.625
I will save that
for my therapy animal.

51:40.291 --> 51:41.333
Yeah,

51:41.416 --> 51:43.291
- you need a therapy animal.
- Oh, yeah.

51:43.375 --> 51:47.000
Well, you need
a herd of therapy animals.

51:47.083 --> 51:51.083
Yeah. You need a whole
migration of therapy animals.

51:53.125 --> 51:54.666
- [Judy gasps]
- [Nick strains]

51:54.750 --> 51:55.791
[both gasping]

52:22.833 --> 52:23.833
[grunts]

52:24.666 --> 52:25.916
Carrots?

52:27.333 --> 52:28.416
[sighs]

52:36.250 --> 52:37.250
[beeping]

52:38.541 --> 52:39.541
[snorts]

52:40.083 --> 52:41.208
- [snorts]
- [beeping continues]

52:42.291 --> 52:43.125
Hmm.

52:46.083 --> 52:47.250
[growls, snorts]

52:53.833 --> 52:55.541
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

52:58.250 --> 52:59.958
[creaking]

53:03.833 --> 53:06.208
[creaking]

53:08.458 --> 53:09.958
Hey, Carrots?

53:16.666 --> 53:17.666
[Judy] Huh.

53:17.750 --> 53:19.375
[squelches, splashes]

53:19.458 --> 53:20.625
Ew.

53:20.708 --> 53:22.125
[breathes shakily]

53:41.833 --> 53:44.333
[motorcycle rumbling]

53:48.291 --> 53:49.875
Uh, Carrots?

53:51.333 --> 53:52.333
Ugh.

53:52.416 --> 53:53.541
[gasps]

53:56.000 --> 53:57.375
- Huh?
- [Nick gasps]

53:57.458 --> 53:58.708
Carrots!

54:00.375 --> 54:01.291
[grunts]

54:22.125 --> 54:24.125
[♪ dramatic music playing]

54:27.750 --> 54:30.500
There was a whole
reptile neighborhood.

54:33.375 --> 54:34.375
Their home...

54:37.125 --> 54:39.375
The lynxes just erased it.

54:39.458 --> 54:41.500
This is what they do.

54:41.583 --> 54:43.833
[Nick panting] We have to go.

54:43.916 --> 54:47.583
They push animals out with
lies so they can have more.

54:47.666 --> 54:48.666
We gotta go.
Carrots, we gotta go!

54:48.750 --> 54:50.166
That's what
the snake's trying to prove.

54:50.250 --> 54:52.000
The ZPD is here.

54:52.083 --> 54:53.416
What?

54:53.500 --> 54:55.458
No one will believe us.
Not without proof.

54:55.541 --> 54:58.000
Leave it. They aren't gonna
just arrest us.

54:58.083 --> 54:59.041
The lynxes want us dead.

54:59.125 --> 55:00.875
We need it to solve the case.

55:00.958 --> 55:03.500
- Judy, just...
- We have to solve the case.

55:03.583 --> 55:05.291
- Nick...
- I don't care about the case!

55:05.375 --> 55:06.375
[♪ music stops]

55:07.125 --> 55:09.666
[stammers, sighs] Judy,
it's not worth dying for.

55:12.708 --> 55:15.375
The world will never be
a better place

55:15.458 --> 55:18.333
if no one is brave enough
to do the right thing.

55:18.416 --> 55:20.208
The world is what it is,
Carrots,

55:20.291 --> 55:23.541
and sometimes being a hero...

55:24.541 --> 55:27.416
it just doesn't
make a difference.

55:32.041 --> 55:33.041
[sighs]

55:34.875 --> 55:35.958
I think, uh...

55:38.791 --> 55:41.166
I think maybe...

55:41.250 --> 55:42.375
maybe we...

55:45.291 --> 55:46.875
are different.

55:46.958 --> 55:48.875
- [thuds]
- [grunts]

55:48.958 --> 55:50.416
[yelps]

55:50.958 --> 55:52.500
[yelps]

55:52.583 --> 55:53.583
- [grunts]
- [yelps]

55:55.125 --> 55:56.291
[gasps]

56:00.375 --> 56:01.208
[Judy yelps]

56:01.291 --> 56:02.375
[grunting]

56:02.458 --> 56:03.916
[gasping]

56:05.083 --> 56:06.500
[Nick yelps]

56:08.500 --> 56:09.541
- Mmm.
- [grunts]

56:10.916 --> 56:12.583
[panting]

56:15.291 --> 56:16.250
[Bûcheron grunts]

56:16.333 --> 56:18.125
[gasps, pants]

56:18.708 --> 56:20.166
[grunts, groans]

56:21.541 --> 56:23.750
Oh, my gosh,
I think I just took out a cop.

56:23.833 --> 56:25.208
Uh. Sorry, sir!

56:25.291 --> 56:27.791
- Pawbert?
- Yeah. It's, uh... you know...

56:27.875 --> 56:30.333
- We're the good guys!
- I told you she's helping.

56:30.416 --> 56:31.500
- [floor creaking]
- [Judy yelps]

56:32.291 --> 56:33.916
[panting]

56:35.791 --> 56:37.458
- Come with us.
- [Pawbert grunting]

56:38.208 --> 56:40.041
- Ow.
- We have the fox.

56:40.125 --> 56:42.000
- We have the fox!
- [whimpers]

56:42.708 --> 56:44.208
They already have
your partner.

56:44.958 --> 56:47.000
They can't get you too.

56:47.583 --> 56:49.916
Please. We can stop my family.

56:50.000 --> 56:51.916
- [grunting]
- [groans]

56:52.000 --> 56:53.416
[♪ dramatic music playing]

56:55.458 --> 56:56.291
[grunts]

56:56.375 --> 56:57.791
[pants, yelps]

56:57.875 --> 56:59.083
[Judy grunting]

57:01.416 --> 57:02.625
[Nick whimpering]

57:03.500 --> 57:06.000
- [grunting]
- Judy!

57:06.083 --> 57:07.833
- [groans]
- No, no, no!

57:10.291 --> 57:11.500
I got you.

57:14.541 --> 57:16.125
[panting]

57:24.791 --> 57:26.083
[exhales]

57:26.666 --> 57:28.833
All right. Here we go.

57:33.583 --> 57:35.583
- [engine running]
- [Judy exhales]

57:42.583 --> 57:43.791
What?

57:43.875 --> 57:46.208
[♪ mysterious music playing]

57:54.625 --> 57:55.750
Huh.

57:56.666 --> 57:58.708
- You're not dead! [laughs]
- [yelps]

57:59.250 --> 58:01.208
- She's not dead!
- [chuckles]

58:01.291 --> 58:03.250
[grunts] Sorry, sorry.

58:03.333 --> 58:05.041
I just got
my motorcycle license.

58:08.458 --> 58:09.458
Nick?

58:10.208 --> 58:11.625
They, uh...

58:12.291 --> 58:13.583
They caught him.

58:17.083 --> 58:20.750
But out here,
no one's gonna catch us.

58:23.666 --> 58:24.666
[grunting]

58:25.750 --> 58:27.541
Mayor Winddancer.

58:28.875 --> 58:29.875
[snorts]

58:34.208 --> 58:35.458
Where's the bunny?

58:36.000 --> 58:37.708
I don't know.

58:37.791 --> 58:39.750
But, you know, she's a rabbit.

58:39.833 --> 58:41.625
So maybe you can
pull her out of your hat.

58:42.958 --> 58:44.333
I'm not wearing a hat.

58:44.416 --> 58:45.750
He's messing with you, sir.

58:45.833 --> 58:47.750
I knew that.
Get him out of here.

58:49.083 --> 58:50.125
No.

58:53.000 --> 58:54.125
[♪ tense music playing]

58:54.208 --> 58:56.791
Where are they, Mr. Wilde?

58:58.541 --> 58:59.875
[sighs]

58:59.958 --> 59:01.416
Begin the expansion.

59:01.500 --> 59:02.833
Freeze Marsh Market.

59:02.916 --> 59:04.958
- Flush everyone out.
- What? No, you can't--

59:05.041 --> 59:10.541
Water folk, like foxes,
are lesser mammals.

59:10.625 --> 59:13.708
If I say they helped
a dangerous snake,

59:13.791 --> 59:16.125
no one will care what we do.

59:16.208 --> 59:18.000
[Nick groans]

59:18.083 --> 59:20.916
You're going
to a dark cell, Mr. Wilde.

59:21.000 --> 59:24.041
Just long enough
to read the headline

59:24.125 --> 59:26.291
of your partner's demise.

59:26.791 --> 59:27.666
[Nick groans]

59:29.000 --> 59:32.666
You should've left town
when you had the chance.

59:32.750 --> 59:34.125
[engine starts]

59:39.333 --> 59:40.333
[sighs]

59:41.500 --> 59:42.833
Dad.

59:42.916 --> 59:46.208
Fur from whoever's helping
the bunny and the snake.

59:48.791 --> 59:50.750
Find Pawbert.

59:52.875 --> 59:55.000
[Pawbert]
Almost to me hideout.

59:55.083 --> 59:56.375
[chuckles]

59:56.458 --> 59:57.541
Snake in the hole.

59:57.625 --> 59:58.458
Ooh. Yeah, yeah.

59:58.541 --> 59:59.541
[Judy] Oh!

01:00:00.666 --> 01:00:01.500
Oh!

01:00:01.583 --> 01:00:03.958
We shall succeed, Judy Hopps.

01:00:04.041 --> 01:00:07.416
We'll stop the Lynxleys
and save your partner.

01:00:07.916 --> 01:00:10.041
I'm sorry. You are...

01:00:10.125 --> 01:00:12.625
Oh. Gary. Gary the Snake.

01:00:12.708 --> 01:00:14.166
And your last name?

01:00:14.250 --> 01:00:15.500
De'Snake.

01:00:15.583 --> 01:00:18.041
Everything is gonna be okay.

01:00:18.125 --> 01:00:20.291
[gagging]

01:00:22.250 --> 01:00:23.250
[clears throat]

01:00:24.791 --> 01:00:25.791
[chuckles nervously]

01:00:26.708 --> 01:00:30.416
[Gary chuckles] Teaming up
with you is very exciting.

01:00:30.500 --> 01:00:33.500
Ooh! Uh,
don't worry about my fang.

01:00:33.583 --> 01:00:36.083
I got my own anti-venom pen.

01:00:36.166 --> 01:00:37.458
Stops the toxin.

01:00:37.541 --> 01:00:39.750
[anti-venom pen] <i>Stab me</i>
<i>straight into the heart.</i>

01:00:39.833 --> 01:00:40.750
[Judy chuckles nervously]

01:00:40.833 --> 01:00:42.750
[chuckles, gasps]

01:00:44.166 --> 01:00:46.958
Welcome to my oasis...
[chuckles]

01:00:47.041 --> 01:00:49.000
...away from my evil family.

01:00:49.083 --> 01:00:51.541
I like to come here,
just kind of veg out.

01:00:51.625 --> 01:00:52.916
Ooh!

01:00:53.000 --> 01:00:55.083
- Get with all my cat stuff.
- Wow.

01:00:55.166 --> 01:00:57.666
- No! That's actually vintage.
- Awesome.

01:00:57.750 --> 01:00:59.416
[chuckles] No!
If you could just not.

01:00:59.500 --> 01:01:01.166
- [Gary] Ooh!
- No! No, please don't.

01:01:01.250 --> 01:01:02.083
- Wow!
- Oh, my gosh.

01:01:02.166 --> 01:01:03.833
- Mammals get the best stuff.
- No.

01:01:03.916 --> 01:01:05.333
- What's this do?
- Wait, not that.

01:01:05.416 --> 01:01:07.208
[purring]

01:01:07.291 --> 01:01:09.500
Turn it off. Turn it off.
Turn it off. Turn it off.

01:01:09.583 --> 01:01:10.583
[clears throat]

01:01:11.166 --> 01:01:14.583
So, we should probably
get to the journal, hmm?

01:01:15.125 --> 01:01:18.083
How did you become partners?

01:01:18.166 --> 01:01:20.125
Oh, when I found out
the journal

01:01:20.208 --> 01:01:22.125
was going to be
on display at the Gala,

01:01:22.208 --> 01:01:25.708
I sent his family an anonymous
letter asking to see it.

01:01:25.791 --> 01:01:28.875
Luckily, they make Pawbert
work in the mail room,

01:01:28.958 --> 01:01:30.958
so he read it first.

01:01:31.041 --> 01:01:33.583
I got him smuggled in
from overseas.

01:01:33.666 --> 01:01:35.833
Seven days in a crate.

01:01:35.916 --> 01:01:39.416
But if I fix things for
my family, it'll be worth it.

01:01:39.500 --> 01:01:42.750
Then we'll fix things
for your partner too.

01:01:42.833 --> 01:01:44.958
[♪ sentimental music playing]

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:48.833
Hey.

01:01:48.916 --> 01:01:51.875
I know coming with us
was hard,

01:01:52.833 --> 01:01:55.041
but we're gonna
help your partner,

01:01:55.125 --> 01:01:57.500
the same way
we're gonna help the city.

01:01:58.500 --> 01:02:02.666
We stop my family
and show everyone the truth.

01:02:03.250 --> 01:02:04.875
Are you ready?

01:02:04.958 --> 01:02:06.833
Light the fire.

01:02:16.125 --> 01:02:19.125
How much do you know?

01:02:19.208 --> 01:02:23.041
Well, uh, that his family
was framed,

01:02:23.125 --> 01:02:25.833
and there's some secret
hidden in the metal cover

01:02:25.916 --> 01:02:28.458
that only a snake can see.

01:02:29.125 --> 01:02:34.166
Not just any snake,
a heat-sensing pit viper.

01:02:35.166 --> 01:02:38.083
All it takes
is a little warmth.

01:02:39.250 --> 01:02:42.416
I just... I don't understand.

01:02:42.500 --> 01:02:44.541
Why would
your great-grandfather

01:02:44.625 --> 01:02:46.708
hide a secret for a snake?

01:02:46.791 --> 01:02:49.125
He didn't.

01:02:49.875 --> 01:02:50.875
I...

01:02:51.500 --> 01:02:52.583
[gasps]

01:02:53.708 --> 01:02:55.708
It wasn't his journal.

01:02:57.250 --> 01:02:59.000
That's the secret.

01:02:59.833 --> 01:03:02.958
<i>Zootopia wasn't created</i>
<i>by a mammal.</i>

01:03:03.875 --> 01:03:07.458
<i>It was created by a snake.</i>

01:03:07.541 --> 01:03:09.750
[Pawbert]
<i>Gary's great-grandmother.</i>

01:03:11.958 --> 01:03:13.541
<i>She wanted to make the city</i>
<i>a place</i>

01:03:13.625 --> 01:03:16.250
<i>where all animals</i>
<i>felt welcome.</i>

01:03:18.666 --> 01:03:21.458
<i>So she invented</i>
<i>her weather walls</i>

01:03:21.541 --> 01:03:23.750
<i>to help everyone.</i>

01:03:29.125 --> 01:03:31.375
<i>She just needed an investor.</i>

01:03:32.541 --> 01:03:33.791
<i>A partner.</i>

01:03:35.458 --> 01:03:37.541
<i>But when my great-grandfather</i>

01:03:37.625 --> 01:03:39.958
<i>saw what her idea</i>
<i>could be worth...</i>

01:03:43.750 --> 01:03:47.291
<i>he plotted to steal her plans</i>
<i>for himself.</i>

01:03:53.916 --> 01:03:55.958
<i>So he committed a murder...</i>

01:03:58.291 --> 01:04:00.500
<i>his own maid...</i>

01:04:03.041 --> 01:04:05.333
<i>and framed</i>
<i>Gary's great-grandmother.</i>

01:04:05.416 --> 01:04:07.041
[clamoring]

01:04:07.125 --> 01:04:09.208
<i>And because she was a snake,</i>

01:04:10.125 --> 01:04:12.000
<i>everyone believed his lie.</i>

01:04:13.500 --> 01:04:18.583
<i>Soon, no reptiles</i>
<i>were welcome.</i>

01:04:19.583 --> 01:04:21.291
<i>And over time,</i>

01:04:21.375 --> 01:04:22.833
<i>my great-grandfather</i>

01:04:22.916 --> 01:04:28.125
<i>buried the reptile</i>
<i>neighborhood in snow.</i>

01:04:31.166 --> 01:04:36.750
<i>And he died believing no one</i>
<i>could ever uncover his crimes.</i>

01:04:37.791 --> 01:04:38.875
<i>But...</i>

01:04:40.708 --> 01:04:43.125
<i>he was wrong.</i>

01:04:45.583 --> 01:04:49.125
[Judy]
<i>Her original patent was saved.</i>

01:04:50.375 --> 01:04:52.125
<i>That's what</i>
<i>you're looking for.</i>

01:04:52.208 --> 01:04:53.916
<i>She hid it in her home.</i>

01:04:54.833 --> 01:04:58.541
<i>Find her home,</i>
<i>find her patent.</i>

01:05:07.208 --> 01:05:10.208
We just didn't know
where her home was buried

01:05:11.375 --> 01:05:13.750
until now.

01:05:15.250 --> 01:05:17.083
[Pawbert] My family's land?

01:05:17.166 --> 01:05:22.250
But under all that snow,
how are we gonna find it?

01:05:22.833 --> 01:05:23.833
Wait.

01:05:23.916 --> 01:05:25.333
Clock tower.

01:05:25.416 --> 01:05:27.625
Her neighborhood,
the reptile neighborhood,

01:05:27.708 --> 01:05:28.875
had a clock tower.

01:05:28.958 --> 01:05:30.625
It lights up like a beacon.

01:05:30.708 --> 01:05:34.125
If it wasn't fully buried,
maybe we could see it.

01:05:34.208 --> 01:05:35.750
Follow it to her home.

01:05:35.833 --> 01:05:37.791
Except my great-grandfather
turned off the power.

01:05:37.875 --> 01:05:39.375
But we have the plans

01:05:39.458 --> 01:05:41.250
that show us
how to turn it back on.

01:05:41.333 --> 01:05:43.291
Oh! Ooh! Hmm.

01:05:43.375 --> 01:05:45.791
The power switch
to her whole neighborhood

01:05:45.875 --> 01:05:48.583
was in the original
control room.

01:05:48.666 --> 01:05:51.208
All right! And where is that?

01:05:51.291 --> 01:05:53.000
Inside the oldest wall
of the city.

01:05:53.083 --> 01:05:55.458
The Desert Tundratown
weather wall.

01:05:55.541 --> 01:05:58.583
We get inside,
turn on that switch,

01:05:58.666 --> 01:06:00.125
light the clock tower,

01:06:00.208 --> 01:06:04.166
- we find her house.
- We find her patent.

01:06:04.250 --> 01:06:07.000
And my family
is finally coming home.

01:06:07.500 --> 01:06:09.666
We will succeed, Judy Hopps.

01:06:09.750 --> 01:06:12.625
We shall succeed!

01:06:14.791 --> 01:06:16.208
[Kitty gasps] I found him.

01:06:18.083 --> 01:06:19.541
Get me Hoggbottom.

01:06:19.625 --> 01:06:21.166
[alarm buzzes]

01:06:21.250 --> 01:06:22.291
[groans]

01:06:22.375 --> 01:06:27.375
Ooh! It's Nicholas Wilde.
Big-time cop, huh?

01:06:27.458 --> 01:06:29.500
I'll see you
at the lunch table.

01:06:30.083 --> 01:06:32.625
I'm gonna tie your tail
in a knot.

01:06:32.708 --> 01:06:33.583
Hoggbottom--

01:06:33.666 --> 01:06:35.708
What are you looking at,
butthead?

01:06:35.791 --> 01:06:38.583
This is a mistake.
It's a setup. It's the lynxes.

01:06:38.666 --> 01:06:40.208
Listen to me. Please.

01:06:40.291 --> 01:06:43.083
I know we have had
our differences, right?

01:06:43.166 --> 01:06:45.875
But I've always
respected you--

01:06:46.708 --> 01:06:49.291
You don't respect anyone.

01:06:49.375 --> 01:06:51.166
[grunting]

01:06:51.250 --> 01:06:53.625
Phone. It's Milton Lynxley.

01:06:53.708 --> 01:06:55.791
He's got
the rabbit's location.

01:06:55.875 --> 01:06:58.291
Whatever he says,
it's a lie, Hoggbottom.

01:06:58.375 --> 01:06:59.958
Hoggbottom, listen to me!

01:07:00.041 --> 01:07:01.083
Oh, God.

01:07:01.166 --> 01:07:03.375
[grunting]

01:07:03.458 --> 01:07:08.041
[Nibbles] Nicholas Wilde!

01:07:09.750 --> 01:07:12.250
What are the chances? [laughs]

01:07:13.458 --> 01:07:15.416
You know, this is
my first time in prison,

01:07:15.500 --> 01:07:16.916
and I gotta say,

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:19.500
their food is on point.

01:07:19.583 --> 01:07:22.041
[sighs] How are you even here?

01:07:22.125 --> 01:07:23.333
Destiny.

01:07:23.416 --> 01:07:25.583
Plus an arrest. [chuckles]

01:07:25.666 --> 01:07:27.708
But it looks like
Judith got away.

01:07:27.791 --> 01:07:31.875
Was that decision mutual?

01:07:31.958 --> 01:07:33.166
- [sighs]
- Oh.

01:07:33.250 --> 01:07:36.833
Sensing trouble in paradise.
Wanna talk about it?

01:07:36.916 --> 01:07:39.166
What I want
is to get out of here.

01:07:39.250 --> 01:07:40.583
[Nibbles]
Right, your big plan.

01:07:40.666 --> 01:07:44.000
Lay low on Outback Island
sipping piña koalas.

01:07:44.083 --> 01:07:46.875
Except you can't trust koalas,
'cause they got four thumbs.

01:07:46.958 --> 01:07:49.250
Did a whole episode about it
on my podcast.

01:07:49.333 --> 01:07:52.083
It was called
"They Got Four Thumbs."

01:07:52.166 --> 01:07:54.208
But you know what? At least
they ain't platypuses.

01:07:54.291 --> 01:07:55.291
- [laughs]
- Wait. Can you just...

01:07:55.375 --> 01:07:57.708
Can you please
just let me concentrate?

01:07:57.791 --> 01:07:58.958
Roger that.

01:07:59.041 --> 01:08:00.000
[crunching]

01:08:04.083 --> 01:08:06.250
- Just talk to me, dude!
- [nail cracks]

01:08:06.333 --> 01:08:07.166
[sighs]

01:08:07.250 --> 01:08:09.541
What's the last thing
she said to you?

01:08:09.625 --> 01:08:10.708
[sighs]

01:08:10.791 --> 01:08:12.208
She, um...

01:08:12.291 --> 01:08:18.208
Uh, she said
maybe we are too different.

01:08:18.791 --> 01:08:19.708
[Nibbles] Hmm.

01:08:19.791 --> 01:08:22.458
And what did you say
before that?

01:08:23.083 --> 01:08:25.333
I said the case
isn't worth dying for.

01:08:25.416 --> 01:08:26.458
Mmm.

01:08:26.541 --> 01:08:27.541
Like, uh...

01:08:28.625 --> 01:08:33.083
like, you know, as in it isn't
worth her dying for because...

01:08:35.041 --> 01:08:37.458
because solitary animals
like me

01:08:37.541 --> 01:08:40.041
don't have real friends.

01:08:41.208 --> 01:08:44.625
And I... I...
I don't want to lose her.

01:08:46.458 --> 01:08:47.583
So, I just...

01:08:49.375 --> 01:08:50.750
I don't know how to say that.

01:08:52.166 --> 01:08:53.166
[Nibbles sighs]

01:08:53.250 --> 01:08:55.791
You know what, bud?
I think you just did.

01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:58.333
Wait, how'd you do that?

01:08:58.416 --> 01:09:00.166
Well, I opened my arms,

01:09:00.250 --> 01:09:03.000
put them around you
and then I squeezed.

01:09:03.083 --> 01:09:06.333
It's called a hug.
Do foxes not have hugs?

01:09:06.958 --> 01:09:08.333
Oh! [laughs]

01:09:08.416 --> 01:09:10.791
The lock.
Yeah, that's Beave 101.

01:09:10.875 --> 01:09:12.916
[Hoggbottom]
The rabbit's in Desert Dunes.

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:13.833
Roll out!

01:09:13.916 --> 01:09:15.583
[Truffler] Hit it. Roll out!

01:09:15.666 --> 01:09:17.708
Your partner needs you,

01:09:17.791 --> 01:09:20.166
and Nibbles Maplestick
is gonna get you to her.

01:09:21.750 --> 01:09:26.125
Hey! It's the fox dad!
And the woodchuck!

01:09:26.208 --> 01:09:28.750
Woodchuck? I'm a beaver!
Call me that again--

01:09:28.833 --> 01:09:30.083
- [alarm blaring]
- Oops.

01:09:30.166 --> 01:09:31.958
Okay, go! We gotta go!
Here we go!

01:09:32.750 --> 01:09:34.041
Get back here!

01:09:34.750 --> 01:09:35.583
[gasps]

01:09:35.666 --> 01:09:37.500
Hello, Nicholas.

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:39.583
I hope you like my new home.

01:09:39.666 --> 01:09:41.875
I wove it with my own wool.

01:09:42.750 --> 01:09:44.041
- Jump scare!
- [Nick screams]

01:09:48.083 --> 01:09:49.958
[chuckles] <i>Adios!</i>

01:09:50.500 --> 01:09:52.083
[cell doors opening]

01:09:52.166 --> 01:09:55.291
- [cackling]
- Ooh-whee!

01:09:56.458 --> 01:09:57.708
[inmates shouting]

01:09:57.791 --> 01:09:59.166
[rumbling]

01:10:01.583 --> 01:10:02.583
- [cheering]
- We're free!

01:10:04.333 --> 01:10:06.500
- Huh.
- Wheels. We need wheels.

01:10:06.583 --> 01:10:07.416
[horn honks]

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:09.250
- No, no.
- [tires screeching]

01:10:09.333 --> 01:10:10.750
No, no, no, no.

01:10:10.833 --> 01:10:12.291
I am sorry.

01:10:12.375 --> 01:10:15.208
I do not think we can
get to Judy in time to help.

01:10:15.291 --> 01:10:16.916
Unless... [chuckles]

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:19.333
...you happen to know
the fastest driver

01:10:19.416 --> 01:10:21.375
in the history of Zootopia.

01:10:21.458 --> 01:10:22.500
[gasps]

01:10:22.583 --> 01:10:26.208
[♪ exciting music playing]

01:10:28.375 --> 01:10:29.375
[♪ music stops]

01:10:37.666 --> 01:10:40.750
[chuckles] Hey, Flash,
Flash Hundred Yard Dash.

01:10:40.833 --> 01:10:41.750
Partner's in trouble.

01:10:41.833 --> 01:10:43.291
Need to get across town,
ignore the laws.

01:10:43.791 --> 01:10:44.791
No...

01:10:47.333 --> 01:10:48.791
problem.

01:10:48.875 --> 01:10:50.541
[chuckles] Let's hit it.

01:10:51.375 --> 01:10:52.708
[♪ languid music playing]

01:10:52.791 --> 01:10:54.250
Hey.

01:10:54.333 --> 01:10:56.250
- Glad you're here.
- I gotta tell ya,

01:10:56.333 --> 01:10:58.791
I'm not convinced
a sloth is our most reliable--

01:10:58.875 --> 01:11:00.291
[both screaming]

01:11:00.375 --> 01:11:02.708
[Nick] Oh, yeah! Whoo-hoo!

01:11:02.791 --> 01:11:04.625
[laughing]

01:11:05.583 --> 01:11:07.041
To turn on the clock tower,

01:11:07.125 --> 01:11:08.375
and light the way
to your great-grandma's home

01:11:08.458 --> 01:11:09.708
so we can find her patent,

01:11:09.791 --> 01:11:12.791
we need to reach the power
control room through here.

01:11:12.875 --> 01:11:14.083
But we have to move quickly
or we're never--

01:11:14.166 --> 01:11:16.583
We shall succeed, Judy Hopps.

01:11:16.666 --> 01:11:18.166
Look, Gary,
if we don't over-prepare,

01:11:18.250 --> 01:11:20.125
we're underprepared
and I don't...

01:11:21.166 --> 01:11:22.833
My family's
been trying to prove

01:11:22.916 --> 01:11:24.458
we're not what everyone thinks

01:11:24.541 --> 01:11:25.875
for a hundred years.

01:11:25.958 --> 01:11:29.083
But even this close,
they'd never want me

01:11:29.166 --> 01:11:32.000
to put the weight of the world
on my shoulders.

01:11:32.083 --> 01:11:34.458
Because I don't have
any shoulders. [laughs]

01:11:36.041 --> 01:11:38.208
We shall succeed.

01:11:42.166 --> 01:11:44.041
I got you, rabbit.

01:11:45.583 --> 01:11:46.583
[mice scream]

01:11:46.666 --> 01:11:48.791
I cannot help Judy
if I don't know where she is,

01:11:48.875 --> 01:11:50.833
which is why I need you
to get on Paul's computer

01:11:50.916 --> 01:11:52.375
<i>and track Hoggbottom.</i>

01:11:52.458 --> 01:11:54.125
You are an escaped fugitive.

01:11:54.208 --> 01:11:56.541
I could get fired
for even talking to you.

01:11:56.625 --> 01:11:58.916
They're gonna put her
to sleep! Do it!

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:00.000
Okay!

01:12:01.541 --> 01:12:02.375
Hmm.

01:12:02.458 --> 01:12:04.875
Did you try restarting it?
Mm-hmm.

01:12:04.958 --> 01:12:06.250
Have you tried
not being an idiot?

01:12:06.333 --> 01:12:08.833
Hey, Paul.
I got you some donuts.

01:12:08.916 --> 01:12:10.291
- Oh!
- [Paul growling]

01:12:10.375 --> 01:12:11.875
- Oh, no!
- Thanks, Clawhauser.

01:12:11.958 --> 01:12:14.208
[Nick] <i>Clawhauser! Location!</i>

01:12:17.333 --> 01:12:19.166
[Pawbert] Oh, no.

01:12:19.250 --> 01:12:21.416
I think we're gonna have to
go through the festival.

01:12:21.500 --> 01:12:22.625
[Judy] Festival?

01:12:23.375 --> 01:12:24.833
[crowd cheering]

01:12:25.833 --> 01:12:28.333
- [siren wailing]
- [gasps]

01:12:28.416 --> 01:12:30.208
The phone's
the first thing they track.

01:12:30.291 --> 01:12:32.041
Go! Go!

01:12:35.416 --> 01:12:37.625
- Clawhauser!
- I am working on it.

01:12:38.541 --> 01:12:41.041
- I got it! No!
- <i>Great, great, great. Now--</i>

01:12:42.708 --> 01:12:43.958
[Pawbert panting]

01:12:49.125 --> 01:12:50.166
[panting]

01:12:51.125 --> 01:12:53.708
Oh. What festival is this?

01:12:57.291 --> 01:12:58.500
Yeah!

01:12:58.583 --> 01:12:59.583
[♪ upbeat music playing]

01:13:01.708 --> 01:13:03.750
Move, move, move!

01:13:05.666 --> 01:13:06.500
[all gasp]

01:13:07.291 --> 01:13:09.375
- Come on!
- Go, go, go!

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:12.041
We are with you, Judy Hopps.

01:13:13.583 --> 01:13:14.416
Ha-ha!

01:13:15.041 --> 01:13:17.083
We meet again, Zebra.

01:13:17.750 --> 01:13:19.541
- [knuckles cracking]
- [Zebros yell]

01:13:19.625 --> 01:13:21.375
- Here come the horns!
- Ow!

01:13:24.083 --> 01:13:26.916
She's going for the door.
She's going for the door!

01:13:27.000 --> 01:13:28.958
[Nick]
<i>Clawhauser, we're out of time.</i>

01:13:30.125 --> 01:13:31.125
[Clawhauser] I got it!

01:13:31.791 --> 01:13:33.541
Desert Tundratown weather wall
access door.

01:13:33.625 --> 01:13:36.041
Desert Tundratown weather wall
access door. Hurry!

01:13:36.125 --> 01:13:39.500
- What is in that wall?
- Power control room.

01:13:39.583 --> 01:13:42.666
But for, like,
some old part of Tundratown.

01:13:42.750 --> 01:13:45.708
[gasps] I know what they're
doing. They'll ruin us.

01:13:48.291 --> 01:13:49.333
[panting]

01:13:49.416 --> 01:13:51.000
[Milton]
<i>No more tranquilizers.</i>

01:13:51.083 --> 01:13:51.958
<i>Put them down.</i>

01:13:52.041 --> 01:13:55.041
- Sir.
- Put them down. Now!

01:13:55.125 --> 01:13:56.666
[♪ tense music playing]

01:13:58.791 --> 01:14:00.333
[Milton] <i>Take the shot.</i>

01:14:00.416 --> 01:14:03.125
<i>Take the shot! Do it!</i>

01:14:04.541 --> 01:14:05.583
Whoa-whoa-whoa!

01:14:05.666 --> 01:14:06.666
[♪ music stops]

01:14:10.541 --> 01:14:12.041
[audio slows, distorts]

01:14:25.541 --> 01:14:26.916
[♪ triumphant music playing]

01:14:30.708 --> 01:14:31.541
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

01:14:31.625 --> 01:14:32.625
Judy!

01:14:32.708 --> 01:14:33.750
[panting]

01:14:37.375 --> 01:14:39.833
- [worker] Snake!
- [Pawbert] Power control room?

01:14:39.916 --> 01:14:41.916
Uh, five flights up.
Come on, hurry!

01:14:42.000 --> 01:14:45.375
[Gary pants]
That is a lot of stairs.

01:14:45.458 --> 01:14:48.708
Way to hustle, bud, I love ya!
I owe ya!

01:14:50.125 --> 01:14:53.208
Whoa, whoa, whoa. It's
turning on. It's turning on!

01:14:53.291 --> 01:14:54.291
[Nibbles grunts]

01:14:55.583 --> 01:14:57.458
No. Nibbles?

01:14:57.541 --> 01:14:59.208
[alarm blaring]

01:15:01.291 --> 01:15:02.666
Nibbles!

01:15:02.750 --> 01:15:03.750
[Judy grunts]

01:15:03.833 --> 01:15:06.500
[gasps] Snake! [grunts]

01:15:06.583 --> 01:15:08.041
Cold!

01:15:08.125 --> 01:15:10.666
[grunting, panting]
It's jammed.

01:15:10.750 --> 01:15:13.458
Don't worry about me.
Find the switch.

01:15:14.125 --> 01:15:15.625
[Judy]
No, no, no, no. Not these.

01:15:15.708 --> 01:15:18.291
It would be, uh... older.

01:15:18.375 --> 01:15:19.541
[♪ tense music playing]

01:15:25.583 --> 01:15:26.916
[Judy straining]

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:27.958
[all straining]

01:15:34.500 --> 01:15:35.791
Can you see it?

01:15:36.541 --> 01:15:38.916
Did we turn on the clock
tower? [breathes heavily]

01:15:39.666 --> 01:15:40.500
[gasps]

01:15:41.666 --> 01:15:43.791
There! [breathes deeply]

01:15:44.416 --> 01:15:45.791
It's there!

01:15:48.291 --> 01:15:49.333
[Pawbert stammers]

01:15:49.416 --> 01:15:52.958
We did it? We can find
the original patent?

01:15:54.958 --> 01:15:56.041
[Judy] Nick?

01:15:56.583 --> 01:15:58.708
The door... It's locked...
We have to...

01:15:58.791 --> 01:16:00.000
How did it lock?

01:16:00.083 --> 01:16:02.291
Nibbles? [straining] Open it.

01:16:03.083 --> 01:16:05.125
[grunts, yells] Nibbles!

01:16:05.208 --> 01:16:06.833
[grunting]

01:16:06.916 --> 01:16:08.666
Dang door stuck on me.

01:16:08.750 --> 01:16:09.750
[Judy sighs]

01:16:09.833 --> 01:16:11.041
Sorry.

01:16:11.125 --> 01:16:13.708
Last case
there was kind of a twist.

01:16:14.291 --> 01:16:15.291
I know.

01:16:15.375 --> 01:16:16.375
[yelps]

01:16:16.458 --> 01:16:17.291
[♪ dramatic music playing]

01:16:17.375 --> 01:16:19.125
- [Pawbert gasping]
- [Judy grunts]

01:16:19.208 --> 01:16:20.875
Oh, my gosh. [chuckles]
I really...

01:16:20.958 --> 01:16:23.208
Oh, my heart is pounding.
[chuckles]

01:16:23.291 --> 01:16:25.083
I thought you knew.
I thought you knew.

01:16:25.166 --> 01:16:26.083
- No. [hisses]
- Whoa.

01:16:26.166 --> 01:16:28.875
- [straining]
- Sorry, partner. [grunts]

01:16:30.083 --> 01:16:32.458
Hate to leave you
out in the cold... [chuckles]

01:16:32.541 --> 01:16:34.708
...but I'm gonna.

01:16:34.791 --> 01:16:37.708
[groans]
Please don't be mad at me.

01:16:38.250 --> 01:16:41.166
But, I mean, you get it.
[chuckles]

01:16:41.250 --> 01:16:44.625
We've always been
on the same page. Me and you!

01:16:44.708 --> 01:16:46.750
Underdogs, right?

01:16:46.833 --> 01:16:50.000
You gotta prove you're as good
as everyone else.

01:16:50.083 --> 01:16:52.166
That you belong.

01:16:52.250 --> 01:16:55.083
[inhales] I know,
it's messed up... [sighs]

01:16:55.166 --> 01:16:57.750
...but this is my chance.

01:16:57.833 --> 01:16:59.291
I have to take it.

01:16:59.958 --> 01:17:02.708
'Cause when I get
to his great-grandma's home,

01:17:02.791 --> 01:17:05.000
and I burn
the original patent,

01:17:05.541 --> 01:17:08.125
I'll finally be something
in my family.

01:17:09.166 --> 01:17:11.541
And I'll finally belong too.

01:17:11.625 --> 01:17:12.916
[Nick, through TV] <i>Judy?</i>

01:17:13.916 --> 01:17:15.875
[Pawbert] Ruh-roh.

01:17:15.958 --> 01:17:17.208
<i>Carrots?</i>

01:17:19.958 --> 01:17:23.208
[clicks tongue, sighs]
No loose ends.

01:17:25.458 --> 01:17:26.875
Bye, partner.7

01:17:30.208 --> 01:17:31.625
Bye, Judy Hopps.

01:17:35.208 --> 01:17:37.416
Pawbert. Please.

01:17:38.208 --> 01:17:41.291
You can be different
than your family.

01:17:43.291 --> 01:17:45.000
I don't want to be different.

01:17:48.250 --> 01:17:50.125
[groans] Nick...

01:17:52.541 --> 01:17:54.125
[Nick] Judy?

01:17:58.208 --> 01:18:00.250
[machinery whirring]

01:18:01.666 --> 01:18:02.833
Judy?

01:18:03.541 --> 01:18:04.958
Nibbles, do you see her?

01:18:05.041 --> 01:18:06.791
No, nothing yet.

01:18:08.125 --> 01:18:09.291
[Nick] Judy.

01:18:09.375 --> 01:18:11.666
Nick. [breathes shakily]

01:18:11.750 --> 01:18:13.291
Ni... [breathes heavily]

01:18:16.500 --> 01:18:18.750
[Gary] We shall succeed,

01:18:19.416 --> 01:18:20.625
Judy Hopps.

01:18:20.708 --> 01:18:24.375
[grunts, stammering]

01:18:26.416 --> 01:18:28.708
It's okay. Judy sent me.

01:18:28.791 --> 01:18:30.875
She needs to find Nick.

01:18:30.958 --> 01:18:31.958
[groans]

01:18:32.916 --> 01:18:35.708
Yep.
Should've seen that coming.

01:18:35.791 --> 01:18:36.791
[groans]

01:18:36.875 --> 01:18:38.416
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:18:39.458 --> 01:18:41.000
[Nick] Judy!

01:18:43.541 --> 01:18:45.375
Nick. [breathes shakily]

01:18:45.458 --> 01:18:51.291
We... shall... succeed.

01:18:51.875 --> 01:18:53.791
[straining]

01:18:54.333 --> 01:18:55.541
[Gary] Judy...

01:18:55.625 --> 01:19:00.166
[breathes shakily]
I can't move.

01:19:00.250 --> 01:19:01.541
[♪ somber music playing]

01:19:01.625 --> 01:19:06.250
And you're too cold to help.

01:19:07.625 --> 01:19:08.916
[Judy] <i>And he's gonna...</i>

01:19:10.208 --> 01:19:11.958
<i>Nick's gonna...</i>

01:19:12.041 --> 01:19:13.583
[Gary straining] <i>Judy...</i>

01:19:14.125 --> 01:19:18.250
<i>The world was</i>
<i>never meant to be</i>

01:19:18.333 --> 01:19:21.625
<i>on one animal's shoulders.</i>

01:19:25.125 --> 01:19:29.666
That's why
my great-grandma wanted

01:19:29.750 --> 01:19:34.458
Zootopia to be for everyone.

01:19:34.958 --> 01:19:40.500
So, we could all help each
other. [breathes shakily]

01:19:41.500 --> 01:19:44.666
I didn't help.

01:19:46.625 --> 01:19:48.166
[Gary straining] <i>You did.</i>

01:19:48.250 --> 01:19:53.041
You chose to help me

01:19:54.750 --> 01:20:01.166
and became
my best warm-blooded friend.

01:20:06.333 --> 01:20:08.375
Very warm.

01:20:10.625 --> 01:20:11.958
[♪ hopeful music playing]

01:20:14.125 --> 01:20:15.416
[Gary sighs]

01:20:18.541 --> 01:20:21.208
Permission to hug?

01:20:26.125 --> 01:20:27.416
[grunts]

01:20:32.666 --> 01:20:34.416
[exhales deeply]

01:20:38.208 --> 01:20:41.791
We're gonna save you
and save your friend.

01:20:42.541 --> 01:20:45.083
- [exhales]
- Judy! [screams]

01:20:45.166 --> 01:20:46.750
Hey, he's gonna eat
that rabbit!

01:20:46.833 --> 01:20:48.708
No, wait! [stammers]
I'm saving her!

01:20:48.791 --> 01:20:50.125
I'm gonna get her
the anti-pen.

01:20:50.208 --> 01:20:51.666
Where is she?

01:20:51.750 --> 01:20:54.541
[sighs] She...
She didn't make it.

01:20:54.625 --> 01:20:55.708
[♪ tense music playing]

01:20:55.791 --> 01:20:59.208
But with snake bites,
you go fast.

01:21:00.666 --> 01:21:01.708
You'll see.

01:21:04.083 --> 01:21:05.375
[grunting]

01:21:05.458 --> 01:21:07.125
[gasps, groans]

01:21:07.750 --> 01:21:09.666
[grunting]

01:21:09.750 --> 01:21:11.583
- [Gary panting]
- [Chèvre yells]

01:21:11.666 --> 01:21:13.375
[gasps] No.

01:21:14.208 --> 01:21:15.208
[all grunting]

01:21:17.375 --> 01:21:18.500
[grunting]

01:21:18.583 --> 01:21:22.541
She's gone, Nick.
Just get it over with!

01:21:22.625 --> 01:21:23.625
[Nick grunts]

01:21:26.166 --> 01:21:28.916
[all grunting]

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:30.208
[Gary gasps]

01:21:32.250 --> 01:21:33.583
- [Higgins grunts]
- [Gary gasps]

01:21:34.250 --> 01:21:35.208
[gasps]

01:21:35.291 --> 01:21:37.583
- [grunting]
- You're done.

01:21:37.666 --> 01:21:40.791
- Know when to quit!
- [grunts]

01:21:40.875 --> 01:21:42.500
[Gary] Anti-venom!

01:21:42.583 --> 01:21:45.750
You can save her with the
anti-venom! Throw me the bag!

01:21:45.833 --> 01:21:47.041
[Bloats grunts]

01:21:47.125 --> 01:21:48.333
Judy!

01:21:50.500 --> 01:21:51.541
[Pawbert groans]

01:21:57.458 --> 01:21:58.625
[both straining]

01:22:03.375 --> 01:22:04.583
[grunts]

01:22:05.500 --> 01:22:07.875
Leave it!
You're gonna kill us both.

01:22:08.458 --> 01:22:10.458
It's not worth dying for.

01:22:11.666 --> 01:22:14.125
Agree to disagree.

01:22:17.416 --> 01:22:18.416
[grunts]

01:22:23.083 --> 01:22:23.916
[Nick yelps]

01:22:25.708 --> 01:22:27.583
[anti-venom pen] <i>Stab me</i>
<i>straight into the heart.</i>

01:22:27.666 --> 01:22:28.791
[gasps]

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:33.333
[groans]

01:22:43.875 --> 01:22:46.125
[screaming]

01:22:46.208 --> 01:22:47.250
[Gary grunts]

01:22:48.041 --> 01:22:49.666
[both grunting]

01:22:49.750 --> 01:22:52.208
[both panting]

01:22:54.083 --> 01:22:55.208
[exhales]

01:22:58.458 --> 01:23:00.666
- I thought... He told me you...
- I was trying to get to you.

01:23:00.750 --> 01:23:02.166
- And I saw you...
- ...that you were...

01:23:04.916 --> 01:23:07.500
I'll help your friend.

01:23:08.541 --> 01:23:12.583
Okay. [stammers] I don't care
that we're different.

01:23:12.666 --> 01:23:14.333
You know? I...

01:23:14.416 --> 01:23:17.708
What I care about is you.

01:23:17.791 --> 01:23:19.458
I care about you.

01:23:21.125 --> 01:23:22.208
Okay?

01:23:23.958 --> 01:23:25.250
And I didn't say it.

01:23:26.083 --> 01:23:27.625
I should've said it.

01:23:27.708 --> 01:23:28.875
But I didn't

01:23:29.500 --> 01:23:30.708
because...

01:23:31.875 --> 01:23:33.791
uh, well... [chuckles]

01:23:33.875 --> 01:23:36.541
...'cause I am
an emotionally insecure

01:23:36.625 --> 01:23:39.291
source of your discomfort,

01:23:39.375 --> 01:23:42.166
who's not good
at expressing his feelings.

01:23:43.833 --> 01:23:45.791
Probably because I've been
on my own my whole life.

01:23:45.875 --> 01:23:47.416
It's not an excuse.
It's just...

01:23:47.500 --> 01:23:50.083
It's why instead
of telling you

01:23:50.166 --> 01:23:53.250
that you're the best thing
that ever happened to me,

01:23:54.000 --> 01:23:56.291
I-I make jokes
about your ears.

01:23:56.375 --> 01:23:58.000
And-And I tell you
that you try too hard,

01:23:58.083 --> 01:23:59.833
when, you know, the truth is

01:23:59.916 --> 01:24:03.041
I just don't want you
to get hurt.

01:24:03.125 --> 01:24:05.333
Because... [breathes deeply]

01:24:05.416 --> 01:24:07.416
Because no one else
in the world

01:24:07.916 --> 01:24:10.750
matters more to me
than you do.

01:24:10.833 --> 01:24:11.916
[♪ sentimental music playing]

01:24:12.875 --> 01:24:15.333
I... I do try too hard
because deep down

01:24:15.416 --> 01:24:17.083
I'm afraid that I am
what everyone thinks I am.

01:24:17.166 --> 01:24:18.791
And I suppress my discomfort
because I'm worried

01:24:18.875 --> 01:24:20.500
it makes me look weak,
and I wanna be strong,

01:24:20.583 --> 01:24:21.666
and I think I'm failing
all the time.

01:24:21.750 --> 01:24:23.166
And I only take
what you say personally

01:24:23.250 --> 01:24:24.666
because you're
the only one in my life

01:24:24.750 --> 01:24:25.958
who ever believed in me,

01:24:26.041 --> 01:24:27.833
even when I don't even
believe in myself.

01:24:27.916 --> 01:24:29.875
[inhales deeply] And I
should have told you that.

01:24:30.750 --> 01:24:33.125
No one else in the world
matters to me

01:24:33.208 --> 01:24:34.458
more than you do either.

01:24:36.708 --> 01:24:37.958
I have unresolved
childhood trauma

01:24:38.041 --> 01:24:38.958
that I refuse to discuss

01:24:39.041 --> 01:24:40.625
because being vulnerable
scares me.

01:24:40.708 --> 01:24:41.875
I make dangerous choices

01:24:41.958 --> 01:24:43.291
because I have an unhealthy
bunny hero complex.

01:24:43.375 --> 01:24:45.916
And I didn't join the ZPD
because I wanted to be a cop.

01:24:46.000 --> 01:24:49.041
I joined because I always
wanted to be part of a pack.

01:24:49.125 --> 01:24:51.416
And the thought of losing you
scares me because...

01:24:52.916 --> 01:24:54.125
because you're my pack.

01:24:55.500 --> 01:24:56.750
I should never have left you,

01:24:56.833 --> 01:24:58.833
and I do need
a herd of therapy animals.

01:24:58.916 --> 01:25:01.333
And I should have told you
that you are the only partner

01:25:01.416 --> 01:25:05.041
I would ever want because...
[sobs] ...you're my fluffle.

01:25:05.708 --> 01:25:07.000
Mmm. Um...

01:25:07.083 --> 01:25:08.833
[crying]
That's a bunch of rabbits.

01:25:08.916 --> 01:25:10.291
[both chuckle]

01:25:10.375 --> 01:25:11.375
[Nibbles] Hmm.

01:25:11.458 --> 01:25:14.541
Now that is what we call
an overshare.

01:25:14.625 --> 01:25:16.666
I'm alive by the way.
I made it.

01:25:17.416 --> 01:25:19.500
Oh! Also that guy
is still alive.

01:25:20.291 --> 01:25:22.083
[cackles]

01:25:22.166 --> 01:25:24.583
- [♪ upbeat music playing]
- Hey! Hey! Thief!

01:25:24.666 --> 01:25:26.750
He's gonna get to
the lost reptile neighborhood,

01:25:26.833 --> 01:25:29.166
find Gary's great-grandma's
patent and destroy it.

01:25:29.250 --> 01:25:31.500
Yeah, I've got no idea what
that means, or who Gary is,

01:25:31.583 --> 01:25:32.625
but let's go!

01:25:33.333 --> 01:25:35.333
- Hopps and Wilde?
- Wilde and Hopps.

01:25:35.416 --> 01:25:37.375
And Nibbles and Gary!

01:25:37.458 --> 01:25:38.500
[gasps] He's Gary.

01:25:38.583 --> 01:25:40.291
Whoa, whoa!

01:25:40.833 --> 01:25:43.875
Thank you. It's for the snake.
He's cold. No fur on him.

01:25:43.958 --> 01:25:45.375
- Why, you little...
- [chuckles] Bye now.

01:25:47.083 --> 01:25:48.208
[panting]

01:25:48.291 --> 01:25:49.875
- You!
- Dad!

01:25:49.958 --> 01:25:50.875
You don't belong
in this family!

01:25:50.958 --> 01:25:51.791
Wait, wait, wait! Dad!

01:25:51.875 --> 01:25:53.916
You will never
belong in this family!

01:25:54.000 --> 01:25:57.125
Wait, wait! I wasn't working
with them. I was helping us.

01:25:57.208 --> 01:25:58.916
[grunting]

01:25:59.000 --> 01:26:01.500
I know where the reptile
neighborhood is buried.

01:26:01.583 --> 01:26:03.083
Where to find the real patent

01:26:03.166 --> 01:26:06.291
that proves that snakes
invented the walls.

01:26:06.375 --> 01:26:09.666
I'm going to destroy it,
for the family.

01:26:10.500 --> 01:26:12.708
For you, Daddy.

01:26:12.791 --> 01:26:15.125
[Winddancer blusters] Uh...

01:26:15.208 --> 01:26:18.083
You want to keep your job,
you say nothing.

01:26:18.875 --> 01:26:19.958
You!

01:26:20.541 --> 01:26:22.708
Maybe you are a Lynxley.

01:26:22.791 --> 01:26:24.208
Take me to the patent.

01:26:24.291 --> 01:26:25.708
[rattling]

01:26:27.000 --> 01:26:29.333
It takes a threesome
to be somethin',

01:26:29.416 --> 01:26:32.333
but a four-way
to bust your doorway.

01:26:33.541 --> 01:26:35.291
[Pawbert exclaims]

01:26:36.333 --> 01:26:38.583
Get to the patent! Destroy it!

01:26:38.666 --> 01:26:40.375
[Pawbert grunting, panting]

01:26:40.458 --> 01:26:42.625
Go! We got this.

01:26:42.708 --> 01:26:46.833
Hey, whiskers,
you're done hurtin' muh city.

01:26:46.916 --> 01:26:48.125
[growling]

01:26:48.208 --> 01:26:49.708
Uh-oh. Tides have turned.

01:26:49.791 --> 01:26:50.875
- [Nibbles grunting]
- [lynxes roar and screech]

01:26:50.958 --> 01:26:52.458
[Nibbles]
Hey, Brian Winddancer!

01:26:52.541 --> 01:26:53.375
[thudding]

01:26:53.458 --> 01:26:57.250
You want to be a hero, or
just play one on TV? Ow!

01:26:57.333 --> 01:26:58.708
[♪ tense music playing]

01:27:00.333 --> 01:27:02.041
[panting]

01:27:09.250 --> 01:27:10.500
[both panting]

01:27:16.458 --> 01:27:17.958
[panting]

01:27:22.708 --> 01:27:24.916
Okay, I go left,
and you go right?

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:27.000
[panting] Uh, yeah.

01:27:28.958 --> 01:27:29.958
Or...

01:27:35.375 --> 01:27:37.458
[panting]

01:27:37.541 --> 01:27:39.791
[engine starts]

01:27:39.875 --> 01:27:42.250
[horn honking]

01:27:42.333 --> 01:27:44.750
- [Pawbert exclaims]
- [Judy laughs]

01:27:44.833 --> 01:27:46.500
[Judy]
You are a horrible driver.

01:27:46.583 --> 01:27:48.083
[Nick] Yes, I am.

01:27:51.208 --> 01:27:52.250
[exclaiming]

01:27:52.333 --> 01:27:53.458
[both laughing]

01:27:56.083 --> 01:27:57.458
[Judy grunts] Whoa.

01:27:58.291 --> 01:27:59.208
[Nick chuckles]

01:28:03.416 --> 01:28:04.833
I'm gonna jump! [grunts]

01:28:09.125 --> 01:28:11.791
[grunts] Zoogetherness. Huh?

01:28:11.875 --> 01:28:13.708
No, never mind.
Forget I said it. Here we go.

01:28:13.791 --> 01:28:15.375
[both grunt]

01:28:15.458 --> 01:28:16.666
- [Nick, Judy grunt]
- [Pawbert exclaims]

01:28:16.750 --> 01:28:19.125
Matches, matches,
matches, matches.

01:28:19.208 --> 01:28:20.916
[panting, gasps]

01:28:21.000 --> 01:28:22.208
Bunnies, we're burrowers.

01:28:22.291 --> 01:28:23.208
Rabbit kick. Hi-yah!

01:28:23.291 --> 01:28:24.500
[Pawbert exclaims]

01:28:25.833 --> 01:28:26.875
[yells]

01:28:26.958 --> 01:28:28.166
[Nick, Judy grunt]

01:28:28.250 --> 01:28:29.458
I'll destroy the patent,

01:28:29.541 --> 01:28:31.875
that town
and everything in it.

01:28:31.958 --> 01:28:35.166
And a dirtbag fox
and a dumb bunny

01:28:35.250 --> 01:28:37.791
will never stand in my way.

01:28:37.875 --> 01:28:39.250
[straining]
She's not a dumb bunny,

01:28:39.333 --> 01:28:41.041
and you're forgetting
one thing.

01:28:41.125 --> 01:28:42.125
What's that?

01:28:42.208 --> 01:28:43.583
[straining]
We're friends with a snake.

01:28:44.666 --> 01:28:46.958
- Howdy, partner. [vocalizes]
- [Pawbert screams]

01:28:47.041 --> 01:28:48.416
- Heads up!
- [grunts]

01:28:49.375 --> 01:28:50.375
[grunts]

01:28:50.458 --> 01:28:53.916
- [groans] Daddy!
- Daddy's busy.

01:28:54.000 --> 01:28:55.833
Brian! Go!

01:28:55.916 --> 01:28:58.583
- You say justice is dead...
- [grunts]

01:28:58.666 --> 01:29:00.833
- ...I say neigh!
- [grunts]

01:29:01.666 --> 01:29:03.000
[yelling]

01:29:03.083 --> 01:29:05.166
Ha-cha! [grunts]

01:29:07.541 --> 01:29:10.500
- [Gary] Here, kitty-kitty.
- No! [grunts]

01:29:10.583 --> 01:29:12.625
It's called an arrest,
sweetheart.

01:29:12.708 --> 01:29:13.708
Boom.

01:29:14.625 --> 01:29:16.208
[screaming]

01:29:16.291 --> 01:29:17.333
[grunts]

01:29:18.625 --> 01:29:23.500
[chuckles] No one
will believe you over us.

01:29:24.166 --> 01:29:26.666
We've always
been better than you.

01:29:26.750 --> 01:29:28.791
And we always will be.

01:29:29.500 --> 01:29:33.208
Nothing you do matters.

01:29:34.458 --> 01:29:37.583
Well, it matters to him.

01:29:37.666 --> 01:29:39.041
[♪ gentle music playing]

01:29:39.125 --> 01:29:40.458
Shall we?

01:30:17.166 --> 01:30:18.208
[gasps]

01:30:22.625 --> 01:30:24.000
[breathes shakily]

01:30:24.083 --> 01:30:25.666
[♪ sentimental music playing]

01:30:33.250 --> 01:30:34.541
[Judy] Hmm.

01:30:44.625 --> 01:30:45.875
[gasps]

01:30:49.833 --> 01:30:51.958
One long sock. [sniffles]

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:16.250
[breathes deeply]

01:31:24.375 --> 01:31:26.541
[gasps] Oh.

01:31:26.625 --> 01:31:28.625
[♪ sentimental music
continues]

01:32:14.458 --> 01:32:15.708
[whirring]

01:32:22.833 --> 01:32:23.916
[ticking]

01:32:29.541 --> 01:32:30.541
[Gary gasps]

01:32:33.583 --> 01:32:38.166
[laughs] I'm gonna burn it all
to the ground!

01:32:38.250 --> 01:32:42.416
I'm a real Lynxley! [laughs]

01:32:43.875 --> 01:32:45.333
[all gasp]

01:32:45.416 --> 01:32:47.958
[panting]

01:32:48.041 --> 01:32:49.083
[all exhale]

01:32:49.666 --> 01:32:52.625
That'll do, pig. That'll do.

01:32:53.416 --> 01:32:54.958
[Moosebridge]
<i>Astonishing news today</i>

01:32:55.041 --> 01:32:58.375
<i>after officers Judy Hopps</i>
<i>and Nicholas Wilde</i>

01:32:58.458 --> 01:33:01.000
along with a pit viper
and a beaver

01:33:01.083 --> 01:33:03.000
foiled another
major conspiracy

01:33:03.083 --> 01:33:06.791
by revealing the true inventor
of the city's weather walls

01:33:06.875 --> 01:33:08.000
was a snake.

01:33:08.083 --> 01:33:10.125
[Growley] <i>While the now</i>
<i>disgraced Lynxley family</i>

01:33:10.208 --> 01:33:12.541
were revealed to have stolen
the original plans

01:33:12.625 --> 01:33:14.250
<i>and covered it up for decades.</i>

01:33:14.333 --> 01:33:18.125
You have not heard the last
of Milton Lyn...

01:33:18.208 --> 01:33:20.125
[Moosebridge]
<i>Their Tundratown expansion</i>

01:33:20.208 --> 01:33:22.958
- <i>now officially canceled.</i>
- [animals cheering]

01:33:23.041 --> 01:33:25.458
[Fuzzby] Some are calling you
the dream team.

01:33:25.541 --> 01:33:26.666
How did you do it?

01:33:27.541 --> 01:33:32.625
Uh... Well, there's a lot of
different animals out there.

01:33:32.708 --> 01:33:35.375
<i>And sometimes,</i>
<i>we start to look</i>

01:33:35.458 --> 01:33:38.250
<i>at all the little reasons</i>
<i>that we're not the same.</i>

01:33:39.208 --> 01:33:40.833
<i>And it makes us worry.</i>

01:33:42.625 --> 01:33:45.625
<i>But maybe if</i>
<i>we just talked to each other,</i>

01:33:45.708 --> 01:33:48.791
<i>if we just tried</i>
<i>to understand one another,</i>

01:33:48.875 --> 01:33:51.041
<i>we would see</i>
<i>that our differences</i>

01:33:51.125 --> 01:33:54.291
<i>don't really make</i>
<i>any difference at all.</i>

01:33:54.375 --> 01:34:00.375
<i>Maybe we'd even see that</i>
<i>what makes me me and you you,</i>

01:34:00.458 --> 01:34:03.625
can make us even stronger.

01:34:04.625 --> 01:34:08.208
And with hard work, you're
gonna get to that by year two!

01:34:08.291 --> 01:34:10.000
[clapping, chattering]

01:34:10.083 --> 01:34:11.083
[whispering] Zebros.

01:34:12.166 --> 01:34:13.916
Actually, my name is Gene.

01:34:14.000 --> 01:34:15.583
[sniffles] My name...

01:34:16.208 --> 01:34:18.125
is also Gene.

01:34:18.208 --> 01:34:19.208
- Zebros!
- Zebros!

01:34:23.416 --> 01:34:24.958
[bunny children laughing]

01:34:25.041 --> 01:34:26.041
[bunny children exclaim]

01:34:26.916 --> 01:34:28.041
He did it!

01:34:28.125 --> 01:34:29.416
[laughter]

01:34:30.333 --> 01:34:31.708
Kids, get off the snake.

01:34:31.791 --> 01:34:34.291
- [bunnies giggling]
- [Clawhauser gasps] Aw!

01:34:35.791 --> 01:34:37.583
- Hi. How is everybody doing?
- [knocking]

01:34:37.666 --> 01:34:39.333
[gasps] Oh!
[stammers] One sec!

01:34:41.166 --> 01:34:43.208
[exclaiming]

01:34:44.416 --> 01:34:45.625
